365 MemberDefImpl(const MemberDefImpl &);
366 MemberDefImpl &operator=(const MemberDefImpl &);
367
368
369 // PIMPL idiom
370 class IMPL;
371 IMPL *m_impl;
372 uchar m_isLinkableCached; // 0 = not cached, 1=FALSE, 2=TRUE
373 uchar m_isConstructorCached; // 0 = not cached, 1=FALSE, 2=TRUE
374 uchar m_isDestructorCached; // 1 = not cached, 1=FALSE, 2=TRUE
375};
376
377MemberDefMutable *createMemberDef(const QCString &defFileName,int defLine,int defColumn,
378 const QCString &type,const QCString &name,const QCString &args,
379 const QCString &excp,Protection prot,Specifier virt,bool stat,
380 Relationship related,MemberType t,const ArgumentList &tal,
381 const ArgumentList &al,const QCString &metaData)
382{
383 return new MemberDefImpl(defFileName,defLine,defColumn,type,name,args,excp,prot,virt,
384 stat,related,t,tal,al,metaData);
385}

389class MemberDefAliasImpl : public DefinitionAliasMixin<MemberDef>
390{
391 public:
392 MemberDefAliasImpl(const Definition *newScope,const MemberDef *md)
393 : DefinitionAliasMixin(newScope,md), m_memberGroup(0) { init(); }
394 virtual ~MemberDefAliasImpl() { deinit(); }
395 virtual DefType definitionType() const { return TypeMember; }
396
397 const MemberDef *getMdAlias() const { return toMemberDef(getAlias()); }
398 MemberDef *getMdAlias() { return toMemberDef(const_cast<Definition*>(getAlias())); }
399 virtual MemberDef *resolveAlias() { return const_cast<MemberDef*>(getMdAlias()); }
400 virtual const MemberDef *resolveAlias() const { return getMdAlias(); }
401
402 virtual MemberDef *deepCopy() const {
403 return createMemberDefAlias(getScope(),getMdAlias());
404 }
405 virtual void moveTo(Definition *) {}
406

809//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
810
811static QCString addTemplateNames(const QCString &s,const QCString &n,const QCString &t)
812{
813 QCString result;
814 QCString clRealName=n;
815 int p=0,i;
816 if ((i=clRealName.find('<'))!=-1)
817 {
818 clRealName=clRealName.left(i); // strip template specialization
819 }
820 if ((i=clRealName.findRev("::"))!=-1)
821 {
822 clRealName=clRealName.right(clRealName.length()-i-2);
823 }
824 while ((i=s.find(clRealName,p))!=-1)
825 {
826 result+=s.mid(p,i-p);
827 uint j=clRealName.length()+i;
828 if (s.length()==j || (s.at(j)!='<' && !isId(s.at(j))))
829 { // add template names
830 //printf("Adding %s+%s\n",qPrint(clRealName),qPrint(t));
831 result+=clRealName+t;
832 }
833 else
834 { // template names already present
835 //printf("Adding %s\n",qPrint(clRealName));
836 result+=clRealName;
837 }
838 p=i+clRealName.length();
839 }
840 result+=s.right(s.length()-p);
841 //printf("addTemplateNames(%s,%s,%s)=%s\n",qPrint(s),qPrint(n),qPrint(t),qPrint(result));
842 return result;
843}
844
845// ol.startMemberDocName has already been done before this is called.
846// when this function returns TRUE, ol.endParameterList will be called.
847//
848// typical sequence:
849// ol.startMemberDoc
850// ol.startMemberDocName
851// --- enter writeDefArgumentList
852// ol.endMemberDocName
853// ol.startParameterList
854// ...
855// ol.startParameterType(first=TRUE)
856// ol.endParameterType
857// ol.startParameterName
858// ol.endParameterName(last==FALSE)
859// ...
860// ol.startParameterType(first=FALSE)
861// ol.endParameterType
862// ol.startParameterName
863// ol.endParameterName(last==TRUE)
864// ...
865// --- leave writeDefArgumentList with return value TRUE
866// ol.endParameterList
867// ol.endMemberDoc(hasArgs=TRUE)
868//
869// For an empty list the function should return FALSE, the sequence is
870// ol.startMemberDoc
871// ol.startMemberDocName
872// --- enter writeDefArgumentList
873// --- leave writeDefArgumentList with return value FALSE
874// ol.endMemberDocName
875// ol.endMemberDoc(hasArgs=FALSE);
876//
877
878static bool writeDefArgumentList(OutputList &ol,const Definition *scope,const MemberDef *md)
879{
880 const ArgumentList &defArgList=(md->isDocsForDefinition()) ?
881 md->argumentList() : md->declArgumentList();
882 //printf("writeDefArgumentList '%s' isDocsForDefinition()=%d\n",qPrint(md->name()),md->isDocsForDefinition());
883 if (!defArgList.hasParameters() || md->isProperty() || md->isTypedef())
884 {
885 return FALSE; // member has no function like argument list
886 }
887
888 if (!md->isDefine()) ol.docify(" ");
889
890 //printf("writeDefArgList(%d)\n",defArgList->count());
891 ol.pushGeneratorState();
892 //ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
893 bool htmlOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputType::Html);
894 bool latexOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputType::Latex);
895 bool docbookOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputType::Docbook);
896 {
897 // html and latex
898 if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
899 if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Latex);
900 if (docbookOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
901
902 ol.endMemberDocName();
903 ol.startParameterList(!md->isObjCMethod());
904 }
905 ol.enableAll();
906 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
907 ol.disable(OutputType::Latex);
908 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
909 {
910 // other formats
911 if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify("("); // start argument list
912 ol.endMemberDocName();
913 }
914 ol.popGeneratorState();
915 //printf("===> name=%s isDefine=%d\n",qPrint(md->name()),md->isDefine());
916
917 QCString cName;
918 if (scope)
919 {
920 cName=scope->name();
921 int il=cName.find('<');
922 int ir=cName.findRev('>');
923 if (il!=-1 && ir!=-1 && ir>il)
924 {
925 cName=cName.mid(il,ir-il+1);
926 //printf("1. cName=%s\n",qPrint(cName));
927 }
928 else if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
929 {
930 cName=tempArgListToString((toClassDef(scope))->templateArguments(),
931 scope->getLanguage());
932 //printf("2. cName=%s\n",qPrint(cName));
933 }
934 else // no template specifier
935 {
936 cName.resize(0);
937 }
938 }
939 //printf("~~~ %s cName=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(cName));
940
941 bool first=TRUE;
942 bool paramTypeStarted=FALSE;
943 bool isDefine = md->isDefine();
944 auto alIt = defArgList.begin();
945 while (alIt!=defArgList.end())
946 {
947 Argument a = *alIt;
948 if (isDefine || first)
949 {
950 ol.startParameterType(first,QCString());
951 paramTypeStarted=TRUE;
952 if (isDefine)
953 {
954 ol.endParameterType();
955 ol.startParameterName(TRUE);
956 }
957 }
958
959 if (!a.attrib.isEmpty() && !md->isObjCMethod()) // argument has an IDL attribute
960 {
961 ol.docify(a.attrib+" ");
962 }
963
964 {
965 QCString n=a.type;
966 if (md->isObjCMethod()) { n.prepend("("); n.append(")"); }
967 if (a.type!="...")
968 {
969 if (!cName.isEmpty()) n=addTemplateNames(n,scope->name(),cName);
970 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),md,n);
971 }
972 }
973
974 if (!isDefine)
975 {
976 if (paramTypeStarted)
977 {
978 ol.endParameterType();
979 paramTypeStarted=FALSE;
980 }
981 ol.startParameterName(defArgList.size()<2);
982 }
983 if (!a.name.isEmpty() || a.type=="...") // argument has a name
984 {
985 ol.disable(OutputType::Latex);
986 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
987 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
988 ol.docify(" "); /* man page */
989 if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
990 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
991 ol.startEmphasis();
992 ol.enable(OutputType::Man);
993 if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Latex);
994 if (docbookOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
995 if (a.name.isEmpty()) ol.docify(a.type); else ol.docify(a.name);
996 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
997 ol.disable(OutputType::Latex);
998 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
999 ol.endEmphasis();
1000 ol.enable(OutputType::Man);
1001 if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Latex);
1002 if (docbookOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
1003 }
1004 if (!a.array.isEmpty())
1005 {
1006 ol.docify(a.array);
1007 }
1008 if (!a.defval.isEmpty()) // write the default value
1009 {
1010 QCString n=a.defval;
1011 if (!cName.isEmpty()) n=addTemplateNames(n,scope->name(),cName);
1012 ol.docify(" = ");
1013
1014 ol.startTypewriter();
1015 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),md,n,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE);
1016 ol.endTypewriter();
1017
1018 }
1019 ++alIt;
1020 if (alIt!=defArgList.end())
1021 {
1022 a = *alIt;
1023 if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify(", "); // there are more arguments
1024 if (!isDefine)
1025 {
1026 QCString key;
1027 if (md->isObjCMethod() && a.attrib.length()>=2)
1028 {
1029 //printf("Found parameter keyword %s\n",a.qPrint(attrib));
1030 // strip [ and ]
1031 key=a.attrib.mid(1,a.attrib.length()-2);
1032 if (key!=",") key+=":"; // for normal keywords add colon
1033 }
1034 ol.endParameterName(FALSE,FALSE,!md->isObjCMethod());
1035 if (paramTypeStarted)
1036 {
1037 ol.endParameterType();
1038 }
1039 ol.startParameterType(FALSE,key);
1040 paramTypeStarted=TRUE;
1041 }
1042 else // isDefine
1043 {
1044 ol.endParameterName(FALSE,FALSE,TRUE);
1045 }
1046 }
1047 first=FALSE;
1048 }
1049 ol.pushGeneratorState();
1050 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
1051 ol.disable(OutputType::Latex);
1052 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
1053 if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify(")"); // end argument list
1054 ol.enableAll();
1055 if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
1056 if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Latex);
1057 if (docbookOn) ol.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
1058 if (first) ol.startParameterName(defArgList.size()<2);
1059 ol.endParameterName(TRUE,defArgList.size()<2,!md->isObjCMethod());
1060 ol.popGeneratorState();
1061 if (!md->extraTypeChars().isEmpty())
1062 {
1063 ol.docify(md->extraTypeChars());
1064 }
1065 if (defArgList.constSpecifier())
1066 {
1067 ol.docify(" const");
1068 }
1069 if (defArgList.volatileSpecifier())
1070 {
1071 ol.docify(" volatile");
1072 }
1073 if (defArgList.refQualifier()==RefQualifierLValue)
1074 {
1075 ol.docify(" &");
1076 }
1077 else if (defArgList.refQualifier()==RefQualifierRValue)
1078 {
1079 ol.docify(" &&");
1080 }
1081 if (!defArgList.trailingReturnType().isEmpty())
1082 {
1083 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
1084 scope, // scope
1085 md->getBodyDef(), // fileScope
1086 md, // self
1087 defArgList.trailingReturnType(), // text
1088 FALSE // autoBreak
1089 );
1090
1091 }
1092 return TRUE;
1093}
1094
1095static void writeExceptionListImpl(
1096 OutputList &ol, const ClassDef *cd, const MemberDef *md, QCString const& exception)
1097{
1098 // this is ordinary exception spec - there must be a '('
1099 //printf("exception='%s'\n",qPrint(exception));
1100 int index = exception.find('(');
1101 if (index!=-1)
1102 {
1103 ol.exceptionEntry(exception.left(index),false);
1104 ++index; // paren in second column so skip it here
1105 for (int comma = exception.find(',', index); comma!=-1; )
1106 {
1107 ++comma; // include comma
1108 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,
1109 exception.mid(index,comma-index));
1110 ol.exceptionEntry(QCString(),false);
1111 index=comma;
1112 comma = exception.find(',', index);
1113 }
1114 int close = exception.find(')', index);
1115 if (close!=-1)
1116 {
1117 QCString type=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(exception.mid(index,close-index));
1118 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,type);
1119 ol.exceptionEntry(QCString(),true);
1120 }
1121 else
1122 {
1123 warn(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),
1124 "missing ) in exception list on member %s",qPrint(md->name()));
1125 }
1126 }
1127 else // Java Exception
1128 {
1129 ol.docify(" ");
1130 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,exception);
1131 }
1132}
1133
1134static void writeExceptionList(OutputList &ol, const ClassDef *cd, const MemberDef *md)
1135{
1136 QCString exception(QCString(md->excpString()).stripWhiteSpace());
1137 if ('{'==exception.at(0))
1138 {
1139 // this is an UNO IDL attribute - need special handling
1140 int index = exception.find(';');
1141 int oldIndex = 1;
1142 while (-1 != index) // there should be no more than 2 (set / get)
1143 {
1144 // omit '{' and ';' -> "set raises (...)"
1145 writeExceptionListImpl(ol,cd,md,exception.mid(oldIndex,index-oldIndex));
1146 oldIndex=index+1;
1147 index = exception.find(';',oldIndex);
1148 }
1149 // the rest is now just '}' - omit that
1150 }
1151 else
1152 {
1153 writeExceptionListImpl(ol,cd,md,exception);
1154 }
1155}

1272 bool hasCallerGraph = false;
1273 bool hasReferencedByRelation = false;
1274 bool hasReferencesRelation = false;
1275 bool explExt = false; // member was explicitly declared external
1276 bool tspec = false; // member is a template specialization
1277 bool groupHasDocs = false; // true if the entry that caused the grouping was documented
1278 bool docsForDefinition = false; // TRUE => documentation block is put before
1279 // definition.
1280 // FALSE => block is put before declaration.
1281 ClassDef *category = 0;
1282 const MemberDef *categoryRelation = 0;
1283 QCString declFileName;
1284 int declLine = -1;
1285 int declColumn = -1;
1286 int numberOfFlowKW = 0;
1287};
1288
1289MemberDefImpl::IMPL::IMPL()
1290{
1291}
1292
1293MemberDefImpl::IMPL::~IMPL()
1294{
1295}
1296
1297void MemberDefImpl::IMPL::init(Definition *d,
1298 const QCString &t,const QCString &a,const QCString &e,
1299 Protection p,Specifier v,bool s,Relationship r,
1300 MemberType mt,const ArgumentList &tal,
1301 const ArgumentList &al,const QCString &meta
1302 )
1303{
1304 classDef=0;
1305 fileDef=0;
1306 redefines=0;
1307 relatedAlso=0;
1308 accessorClass=0;
1309 nspace=0;
1310 memDef=0;
1311 memDec=0;
1312 group=0;
1313 grpId=-1;
1314 enumScope=0;
1315 livesInsideEnum=FALSE;
1316 hasCallGraph = FALSE;
1317 hasCallerGraph = FALSE;
1318 hasReferencedByRelation = FALSE;
1319 hasReferencesRelation = FALSE;
1320 initLines=0;
1321 type=t;
1322 if (mt==MemberType_Typedef) type.stripPrefix("typedef ");
1323 // type.stripPrefix("struct ");
1324 // type.stripPrefix("class " );
1325 // type.stripPrefix("union " );
1326 type=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(type);
1327 args=a;
1328 args=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(args);
1329 if (type.isEmpty()) decl=d->name()+args; else decl=type+" "+d->name()+args;
1330
1331 memberGroup=0;
1332 virt=v;
1333 prot=p;
1334 related=r;
1335 stat=s;
1336 mtype=mt;
1337 exception=e;
1338 proto=FALSE;
1339 annScope=FALSE;
1340 memSpec=0;
1341 annMemb=0;
1342 annEnumType=0;
1343 groupAlias=0;
1344 explExt=FALSE;
1345 tspec=FALSE;
1346 cachedAnonymousType=0;
1347 maxInitLines=Config_getInt(MAX_INITIALIZER_LINES);
1348 userInitLines=-1;
1349 docEnumValues=FALSE;
1350 // copy function template arguments (if any)
1351 tArgList = tal;
1352 //printf("new member al=%p\n",al);
1353 // copy function definition arguments (if any)
1354 defArgList = al;
1355 // convert function declaration arguments (if any)
1356 if (!args.isEmpty())
1357 {
1358 declArgList = *stringToArgumentList(d->getLanguage(),args,&extraTypeChars);
1359 //printf("setDeclArgList %s to %s const=%d\n",qPrint(args),
1360 // qPrint(argListToString(declArgList)),declArgList->constSpecifier);
1361 }
1362 metaData = meta;
1363 templateMaster = 0;
1364 docsForDefinition = TRUE;
1365 isTypedefValCached = FALSE;
1366 cachedTypedefValue = 0;
1367 //inbodyLine = -1;
1368 implOnly=FALSE;
1369 groupMember = 0;
1370 hasDocumentedParams = FALSE;
1371 hasDocumentedReturnType = FALSE;
1372 docProvider = 0;
1373 isDMember = d->getDefFileName().lower().endsWith(".d");
1374}

1380
1381/*! Creates a new member definition.
1382 *
1383 * \param df File containing the definition of this member.
1384 * \param dl Line at which the member definition was found.
1385 * \param dc Column at which the member definition was found.
1386 * \param t A string representing the type of the member.
1387 * \param na A string representing the name of the member.
1388 * \param a A string representing the arguments of the member.
1389 * \param e A string representing the throw clause of the members.
1390 * \param p The protection context of the member, possible values are:
1391 * \c Public, \c Protected, \c Private.
1392 * \param v The degree of 'virtualness' of the member, possible values are:
1393 * \c Normal, \c Virtual, \c Pure.
1394 * \param s A boolean that is true iff the member is static.
1395 * \param r The relationship between the class and the member.
1396 * \param mt The kind of member. See #MemberType for a list of
1397 * all types.
1398 * \param tal The template arguments of this member.
1399 * \param al The arguments of this member. This is a structured form of
1400 * the string past as argument \a a.
1401 * \param meta Slice metadata.
1402 */
1403
1404MemberDefImpl::MemberDefImpl(const QCString &df,int dl,int dc,
1405 const QCString &t,const QCString &na,const QCString &a,const QCString &e,
1406 Protection p,Specifier v,bool s,Relationship r,MemberType mt,
1407 const ArgumentList &tal,const ArgumentList &al,const QCString &meta
1408 ) : DefinitionMixin(df,dl,dc,removeRedundantWhiteSpace(na))
1409{
1410 //printf("MemberDefImpl::MemberDef(%s)\n",na);
1411 m_impl = new MemberDefImpl::IMPL;
1412 m_impl->init(this,t,a,e,p,v,s,r,mt,tal,al,meta);
1413 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1414 m_isConstructorCached = 0;
1415 m_isDestructorCached = 0;
1416}
1417
1418MemberDefImpl::MemberDefImpl(const MemberDefImpl &md) : DefinitionMixin(md)
1419{
1420 m_impl = new MemberDefImpl::IMPL;
1421 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1422 m_isConstructorCached = 0;
1423 m_isDestructorCached = 0;
1424}
1425
1426MemberDef *MemberDefImpl::deepCopy() const
1427{
1428 //MemberDef *result = new MemberDef(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),name());
1429 MemberDefImpl *result = new MemberDefImpl(*this);
1430 // first copy everything by reference
1431 *result->m_impl = *m_impl;
1432 result->m_impl->defArgList = m_impl->defArgList;
1433 result->m_impl->tArgList = m_impl->tArgList;
1434 result->m_impl->typeConstraints = m_impl->typeConstraints;
1435 result->setDefinitionTemplateParameterLists(m_impl->defTmpArgLists);
1436 result->m_impl->declArgList = m_impl->declArgList;
1437 return result;
1438}
1439
1440void MemberDefImpl::moveTo(Definition *scope)
1441{
1442 setOuterScope(scope);
1443 if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
1444 {
1445 m_impl->classDef = toClassDef(scope);
1446 }
1447 else if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile)
1448 {
1449 m_impl->fileDef = toFileDef(scope);
1450 }
1451 else if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1452 {
1453 m_impl->nspace = toNamespaceDef(scope);
1454 }
1455 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1456 m_isConstructorCached = 0;
1457}

1485 m_impl->redefinedBy.inSort(md);

1498
1499bool MemberDefImpl::isReimplementedBy(const ClassDef *cd) const
1500{
1501 if (cd)
1502 {
1503 for (const auto &md : m_impl->redefinedBy)
1504 {
1505 const ClassDef *mcd = md->getClassDef();
1506 if (mcd)
1507 {
1508 if (cd==mcd || cd->isBaseClass(mcd,TRUE))
1509 {
1510 return TRUE;
1511 }
1512 }
1513 }
1514 }
1515 return FALSE;
1516}

1533
1534QCString MemberDefImpl::getOutputFileBase() const
1535{
1536 bool separateMemberPages = Config_getBool(SEPARATE_MEMBER_PAGES);
1537 bool inlineSimpleClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
1538 QCString baseName;
1539
1540 //printf("Member: %s: templateMaster=%p group=%p classDef=%p nspace=%p fileDef=%p\n",
1541 // qPrint(name()),m_impl->templateMaster,m_impl->group,m_impl->classDef,
1542 // m_impl->nspace,m_impl->fileDef);
1543 const NamespaceDef *nspace = getNamespaceDef();
1544 const FileDef *fileDef = getFileDef();
1545 const ClassDef *classDef = getClassDef();
1546 const GroupDef *groupDef = getGroupDef();
1547 if (!m_impl->explicitOutputFileBase.isEmpty())
1548 {
1549 return m_impl->explicitOutputFileBase;
1550 }
1551 else if (templateMaster())
1552 {
1553 return templateMaster()->getOutputFileBase();
1554 }
1555 else if (groupDef)
1556 {
1557 baseName=groupDef->getOutputFileBase();
1558 }
1559 else if (classDef)
1560 {
1561 baseName=classDef->getOutputFileBase();
1562 if (inlineSimpleClasses && classDef->isSimple())
1563 {
1564 return baseName;
1565 }
1566 }
1567 else if (nspace && (nspace->isLinkable() || nspace->isAnonymous()))
1568 {
1569 baseName=nspace->getOutputFileBase();
1570 }
1571 else if (fileDef)
1572 {
1573 baseName=fileDef->getOutputFileBase();
1574 }
1575
1576 if (baseName.isEmpty())
1577 {
1578 warn(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),
1579 "Internal inconsistency: member %s does not belong to any"
1580 " container!",qPrint(name())
1581 );
1582 return "dummy";
1583 }
1584 else if (separateMemberPages && hasDetailedDescription())
1585 {
1586 if (getEnumScope()) // enum value, which is part of enum's documentation
1587 {
1588 baseName+="_"+getEnumScope()->anchor();
1589 }
1590 else
1591 {
1592 baseName+="_"+anchor();
1593 }
1594 }
1595 return baseName;
1596}
1597
1598QCString MemberDefImpl::getReference() const
1599{
1600 QCString ref = DefinitionMixin::getReference();
1601 if (!ref.isEmpty())
1602 {
1603 return ref;
1604 }
1605 const NamespaceDef *nspace = getNamespaceDef();
1606 const FileDef *fileDef = getFileDef();
1607 const ClassDef *classDef = getClassDef();
1608 const GroupDef *groupDef = getGroupDef();
1609 if (templateMaster())
1610 {
1611 return templateMaster()->getReference();
1612 }
1613 else if (groupDef)
1614 {
1615 return groupDef->getReference();
1616 }
1617 else if (classDef)
1618 {
1619 return classDef->getReference();
1620 }
1621 else if (nspace)
1622 {
1623 return nspace->getReference();
1624 }
1625 else if (fileDef)
1626 {
1627 return fileDef->getReference();
1628 }
1629 return "";
1630}
1631
1632QCString MemberDefImpl::anchor() const
1633{
1634 QCString result=m_impl->anc;
1635 if (m_impl->groupAlias) return m_impl->groupAlias->anchor();
1636 if (m_impl->templateMaster) return m_impl->templateMaster->anchor();
1637 if (m_impl->enumScope && m_impl->enumScope!=this) // avoid recursion for C#'s public enum E { E, F }
1638 {
1639 result.prepend(m_impl->enumScope->anchor());
1640 }
1641 if (getGroupDef())
1642 {
1643 if (m_impl->groupMember)
1644 {
1645 result=m_impl->groupMember->anchor();
1646 }
1647 else if (getReference().isEmpty())
1648 {
1649 result.prepend("g");
1650 }
1651 }
1652 return result;
1653}
1654
1655void MemberDefImpl::_computeLinkableInProject()
1656{
1657 bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
1658 bool extractPrivateVirtual = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL);
1659 m_isLinkableCached = 2; // linkable
1660 //printf("MemberDefImpl::isLinkableInProject(name=%s)\n",qPrint(name()));
1661 if (isHidden())
1662 {
1663 //printf("is hidden\n");
1664 m_isLinkableCached = 1;
1665 return;
1666 }
1667 if (templateMaster())
1668 {
1669 //printf("has template master\n");
1670 m_isLinkableCached = templateMaster()->isLinkableInProject() ? 2 : 1;
1671 return;
1672 }
1673 if (isAnonymous())
1674 {
1675 //printf("name invalid\n");
1676 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // not a valid or a dummy name
1677 return;
1678 }
1679 if (!hasDocumentation() || isReference())
1680 {
1681 //printf("no docs or reference\n");
1682 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // no documentation
1683 return;
1684 }
1685 const GroupDef *groupDef = getGroupDef();
1686 const ClassDef *classDef = getClassDef();
1687 if (groupDef && !groupDef->isLinkableInProject())
1688 {
1689 //printf("group but group not linkable!\n");
1690 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // group but group not linkable
1691 return;
1692 }
1693 if (!groupDef && classDef && !classDef->isLinkableInProject())
1694 {
1695 //printf("in a class but class not linkable!\n");
1696 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in class but class not linkable
1697 return;
1698 }
1699 const NamespaceDef *nspace = getNamespaceDef();
1700 const FileDef *fileDef = getFileDef();
1701 if (!groupDef && nspace && m_impl->related==Relationship::Member && !nspace->isLinkableInProject()
1702 && (fileDef==0 || !fileDef->isLinkableInProject()))
1703 {
1704 //printf("in a namespace but namespace not linkable!\n");
1705 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in namespace but namespace not linkable
1706 return;
1707 }
1708 if (!groupDef && !nspace &&
1709 m_impl->related==Relationship::Member && !classDef &&
1710 fileDef && !fileDef->isLinkableInProject())
1711 {
1712 //printf("in a file but file not linkable!\n");
1713 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in file (and not in namespace) but file not linkable
1714 return;
1715 }
1716 if ((!protectionLevelVisible(m_impl->prot) && m_impl->mtype!=MemberType_Friend) &&
1717 !(m_impl->prot==Protection::Private && (m_impl->virt!=Specifier::Normal || isOverride() || isFinal()) && extractPrivateVirtual))
1718 {
1719 //printf("private and invisible!\n");
1720 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // hidden due to protection
1721 return;
1722 }
1723 if (m_impl->stat && classDef==0 && !extractStatic)
1724 {
1725 //printf("static and invisible!\n");
1726 m_isLinkableCached = 1; // hidden due to staticness
1727 return;
1728 }
1729 //printf("linkable!\n");
1730 return; // linkable!
1731}
1732
1733void MemberDefImpl::setDocumentation(const QCString &d,const QCString &docFile,int docLine,bool stripWhiteSpace)
1734{
1735 DefinitionMixin::setDocumentation(d,docFile,docLine,stripWhiteSpace);
1736 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1737}

1739void MemberDefImpl::setBriefDescription(const QCString &b,const QCString &briefFile,int briefLine)
1740{
1741 DefinitionMixin::setBriefDescription(b,briefFile,briefLine);
1742 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1743}
1744
1745void MemberDefImpl::setInbodyDocumentation(const QCString &d,const QCString &inbodyFile,int inbodyLine)
1746{
1747 DefinitionMixin::setInbodyDocumentation(d,inbodyFile,inbodyLine);
1748 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1749}
1750
1751void MemberDefImpl::setHidden(bool b)
1752{
1753 DefinitionMixin::setHidden(b);
1754 m_isLinkableCached = 0;
1755}
1756
1757bool MemberDefImpl::isLinkableInProject() const
1758{
1759 if (m_isLinkableCached==0)
1760 {
1761 MemberDefImpl *that = const_cast<MemberDefImpl*>(this);
1762 that->_computeLinkableInProject();
1763 }
1764 ASSERT(m_isLinkableCached>0);
1765 return m_isLinkableCached==2;
1766}
1767
1768bool MemberDefImpl::isLinkable() const
1769{
1770 if (m_impl->templateMaster)
1771 {
1772 return m_impl->templateMaster->isLinkable();
1773 }
1774 else
1775 {
1776 return isLinkableInProject() || isReference();
1777 }
1778}

1782{
1783 m_impl->defTmpArgLists = lists;
1784}
1785
1786void MemberDefImpl::writeLink(OutputList &ol,
1787 const ClassDef *,const NamespaceDef *,const FileDef *fd,const GroupDef *gd,
1788 bool onlyText) const
1789{
1790 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
1791 bool hideScopeNames = Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES);
1792 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
1793 QCString n = name();
1794 const ClassDef *classDef = getClassDef();
1795 const NamespaceDef *nspace = getNamespaceDef();
1796 if (!hideScopeNames)
1797 {
1798 if (m_impl->enumScope && m_impl->livesInsideEnum && getGroupDef()!=0)
1799 {
1800 n.prepend(m_impl->enumScope->displayName()+sep);
1801 }
1802 if (classDef && gd && !isRelated())
1803 {
1804 n.prepend(classDef->displayName()+sep);
1805 }
1806 else if (nspace && (gd || fd))
1807 {
1808 n.prepend(nspace->displayName()+sep);
1809 }
1810 }
1811
1812 if (isObjCMethod())
1813 {
1814 if (isStatic()) ol.docify("+ "); else ol.docify("- ");
1815 }
1816 if (!onlyText && (isLinkable() || hasDetailedDescription())) // write link
1817 {
1818 if (m_impl->mtype==MemberType_EnumValue && getGroupDef()==0 && // enum value is not grouped
1819 getEnumScope() && getEnumScope()->getGroupDef()) // but its container is
1820 {
1821 const GroupDef *enumValGroup = getEnumScope()->getGroupDef();
1822 ol.writeObjectLink(enumValGroup->getReference(),
1823 enumValGroup->getOutputFileBase(),
1824 anchor(),n);
1825 }
1826 else
1827 {
1828 ol.writeObjectLink(getReference(),getOutputFileBase(),anchor(),n);
1829 }
1830 }
1831 else // write only text
1832 {
1833 ol.startBold();
1834 ol.docify(n);
1835 ol.endBold();
1836 }
1837}
1838
1839static std::mutex g_cachedAnonymousTypeMutex;
1840
1841/*! If this member has an anonymous class/struct/union as its type, then
1842 * this method will return the ClassDef that describes this return type.
1843 */
1844ClassDef *MemberDefImpl::getClassDefOfAnonymousType() const
1845{
1846 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(g_cachedAnonymousTypeMutex);
1847 //printf("%s:getClassDefOfAnonymousType() cache=%s\n",qPrint(name()),
1848 // m_impl->cachedAnonymousType?qPrint(m_impl->cachedAnonymousType->name()):"<empty>");
1849 if (m_impl->cachedAnonymousType) return m_impl->cachedAnonymousType;
1850
1851 QCString cname;
1852 if (getClassDef()!=0)
1853 {
1854 cname=getClassDef()->name();
1855 }
1856 else if (getNamespaceDef()!=0)
1857 {
1858 cname=getNamespaceDef()->name();
1859 }
1860 QCString ltype(m_impl->type);
1861 // strip 'friend' keyword from ltype
1862 ltype.stripPrefix("friend ");
1863
1864 // search for the last anonymous scope in the member type
1865 ClassDef *annoClassDef=0;
1866
1867 // match expression if it contains at least one @1 marker, e.g.
1868 // 'struct A::@1::@2::B' matches 'A::@1::@2::B' but 'struct A::B' does not match.
1869 std::string stype = ltype.str();
1870 static const reg::Ex r(R"([\w@:]*@\d+[\w@:]*)");
1871 reg::Match match;
1872 if (reg::search(stype,match,r)) // found anonymous scope in type
1873 {
1874 QCString annName = match.str();
1875
1876 // if inside a class or namespace try to prepend the scope name
1877 if (!cname.isEmpty() && annName.left(cname.length()+2)!=cname+"::")
1878 {
1879 QCString ts=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(cname+"::"+annName);
1880 annoClassDef=getClass(ts);
1881 }
1882 // if not found yet, try without scope name
1883 if (annoClassDef==0)
1884 {
1885 QCString ts=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(annName);
1886 annoClassDef=getClass(ts);
1887 }
1888 }
1889 m_impl->cachedAnonymousType = annoClassDef;
1890 return annoClassDef;
1891}
1892
1893/*! This methods returns TRUE iff the brief section (also known as
1894 * declaration section) is visible in the documentation.
1895 */
1896bool MemberDefImpl::isBriefSectionVisible() const
1897{
1898 bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
1899 bool extractPrivateVirtual = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL);
1900 bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
1901 bool briefMemberDesc = Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC);
1902 bool repeatBrief = Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF);
1903 bool hideFriendCompounds = Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS);
1904
1905 //printf("Member %s grpId=%d docs=%s file=%s args=%s\n",
1906 // qPrint(name()),
1907 // 0,"", //grpId,grpId==-1?"<none>":Doxygen::memberDocDict[grpId]->data(),
1908 // "", //qPrint(getFileDef()->name()),
1909 // argsString());
1910
1911 auto it = Doxygen::memberGroupInfoMap.find(m_impl->grpId);
1912 bool hasDocs = hasDocumentation();
1913 if (it!=Doxygen::memberGroupInfoMap.end())
1914 {
1915 auto &info = it->second;
1916 //printf("name=%s m_impl->grpId=%d info=%p\n",qPrint(name()),m_impl->grpId,info);
1917 //QCString *pMemGrp = Doxygen::memberDocDict[grpId];
1918 hasDocs = hasDocs ||
1919 // part of a documented member group
1920 (m_impl->grpId!=-1 && !(info->doc.isEmpty() && info->header.isEmpty()));
1921 }
1922
1923 // only include static members with file/namespace scope if
1924 // explicitly enabled in the config file
1925 bool visibleIfStatic = !(getClassDef()==0 &&
1926 isStatic() &&
1927 !extractStatic
1928 );
1929
1930 // only include members is the are documented or
1931 // HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS is NO in the config file
1932 bool visibleIfDocumented = (!hideUndocMembers ||
1933 hasDocs ||
1934 isDocumentedFriendClass()
1935 );
1936
1937 // hide members with no detailed description and brief descriptions
1938 // explicitly disabled.
1939 bool visibleIfEnabled = !(hideUndocMembers &&
1940 documentation().isEmpty() &&
1941 !briefMemberDesc &&
1942 !repeatBrief
1943 );
1944
1945 // Hide friend (class|struct|union) declarations if HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS is true
1946 bool visibleIfFriendCompound = !(hideFriendCompounds &&
1947 isFriend() /*&&
1948 (m_impl->type=="friend class" ||
1949 m_impl->type=="friend struct" ||
1950 m_impl->type=="friend union"
1951 )*/
1952 );
1953
1954 // only include members that are non-private unless EXTRACT_PRIVATE is
1955 // set to YES or the member is part of a group. And as a special case,
1956 // private *documented* virtual members are shown if EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL
1957 // is set to YES
1958 bool visibleIfPrivate = (protectionLevelVisible(protection()) ||
1959 m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Friend ||
1960 (m_impl->prot==Protection::Private &&
1961 (m_impl->virt!=Specifier::Normal || isOverride() || isFinal()) && extractPrivateVirtual && hasDocs)
1962 );
1963
1964 // hide member if it overrides a member in a superclass and has no
1965 // documentation of its own
1966 //bool visibleIfDocVirtual = !reimplements() ||
1967 // !Config_getBool(INHERIT_DOCS) ||
1968 // hasDocs;
1969
1970 // true if this member is a constructor or destructor
1971 bool cOrDTor = isConstructor() || isDestructor();
1972
1973 // hide default constructors or destructors (no args) without
1974 // documentation
1975 bool visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor = !(cOrDTor &&
1976 (m_impl->defArgList.empty() ||
1977 m_impl->defArgList.front().type == "void"
1978 ) &&
1979 !hasDocs
1980 );
1981
1982
1983 //printf("visibleIfStatic=%d visibleIfDocumented=%d visibleIfEnabled=%d "
1984 // "visibleIfPrivate=%d visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor=%d "
1985 // "visibleIfFriendCompound=%d !annScope=%d\n",
1986 // visibleIfStatic,visibleIfDocumented,
1987 // visibleIfEnabled,visibleIfPrivate,visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor,
1988 // visibleIfFriendCompound,!m_impl->annScope);
1989
1990 bool visible = visibleIfStatic && visibleIfDocumented &&
1991 visibleIfEnabled && visibleIfPrivate &&
1992 /*visibleIfDocVirtual &&*/ visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor &&
1993 visibleIfFriendCompound &&
1994 !m_impl->annScope && !isHidden();
1995 //printf("MemberDefImpl::isBriefSectionVisible() %d\n",visible);
1996 return visible;
1997}
1998
1999QCString MemberDefImpl::getDeclType() const
2000{
2001 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
2002 QCString ltype(m_impl->type);
2003 if (lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp && isEnumerate() && isStrong())
2004 {
2005 if (isEnumStruct())
2006 {
2007 ltype+=" struct";
2008 }
2009 else
2010 {
2011 ltype+=" class";
2012 }
2013 }
2014 if (isTypedef() && getLanguage() != SrcLangExt_Slice)
2015 {
2016 ltype.prepend("typedef ");
2017 }
2018 if (isTypeAlias())
2019 {
2020 ltype="using";
2021 }
2022 // strip 'friend' keyword from ltype
2023 ltype.stripPrefix("friend ");
2024 if (ltype=="@") // rename type from enum values
2025 {
2026 ltype="";
2027 }
2028 else
2029 {
2030 if (isObjCMethod())
2031 {
2032 ltype.prepend("(");
2033 ltype.append(")");
2034 }
2035 }
2036 return ltype;
2037}
2038
2039void MemberDefImpl::_writeTemplatePrefix(OutputList &ol, const Definition *def,
2040 const ArgumentList &al, bool writeReqClause) const
2041{
2042 ol.docify("template<");
2043 for (auto it = al.begin(); it!=al.end();)
2044 {
2045 Argument a = *it;
2046 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2047 def, // scope
2048 getFileDef(), // fileScope
2049 this, // self
2050 a.type, // text
2051 FALSE // autoBreak
2052 );
2053 ol.docify(" ");
2054 ol.docify(a.name);
2055 if (a.defval.length()!=0)
2056 {
2057 ol.docify(" = ");
2058 ol.docify(a.defval);
2059 }
2060 ++it;
2061 if (it!=al.end()) ol.docify(", ");
2062 }
2063 ol.docify("> ");
2064 if (writeReqClause && !m_impl->requiresClause.isEmpty())
2065 {
2066 ol.lineBreak();
2067 ol.docify("requires ");
2068 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2069 def, // scope
2070 getFileDef(), // fileScope
2071 this, // self
2072 m_impl->requiresClause, // text
2073 FALSE // autoBreak
2074 );
2075 }
2076}
2077
2078
2079void MemberDefImpl::writeDeclaration(OutputList &ol,
2080 const ClassDef *cd,const NamespaceDef *nd,const FileDef *fd,const GroupDef *gd,
2081 bool inGroup, int indentLevel, const ClassDef *inheritedFrom,const QCString &inheritId) const
2082{
2083 //printf("> %s MemberDefImpl::writeDeclaration() inGroup=%d\n",qPrint(qualifiedName()),inGroup);
2084
2085 // hide enum value, since they appear already as part of the enum, unless they
2086 // are explicitly grouped.
2087 if (!inGroup && m_impl->mtype==MemberType_EnumValue) return;
2088
2089
2090 const Definition *d=0;
2091 ASSERT (cd!=0 || nd!=0 || fd!=0 || gd!=0); // member should belong to something
2092 if (cd) d=cd; else if (nd) d=nd; else if (fd) d=fd; else d=gd;
2093 if (d==gd) // see bug 753608
2094 {
2095 if (getClassDef()) d = getClassDef();
2096 else if (getNamespaceDef()) d = getNamespaceDef();
2097 else if (getFileDef()) d = getFileDef();
2098 }
2099
2100 QCString cname = d->name();
2101 QCString cdname = d->displayName();
2102 QCString cfname = getOutputFileBase();
2103
2104 // search for the last anonymous scope in the member type
2105 ClassDef *annoClassDef=getClassDefOfAnonymousType();
2106
2107 ol.startMemberDeclaration();
2108
2109 // start a new member declaration
2110 bool isAnonType = annoClassDef || m_impl->annMemb || m_impl->annEnumType;
2111 OutputGenerator::MemberItemType anonType = isAnonType ? OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::AnonymousStart :
2112 !m_impl->tArgList.empty() ? OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::Templated :
2113 OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::Normal;
2114 ol.startMemberItem(anchor(), anonType, inheritId);
2115
2116 // If there is no detailed description we need to write the anchor here.
2117 bool detailsVisible = hasDetailedDescription();
2118 bool writeAnchor = (inGroup || getGroupDef()==0) && // only write anchors for member that have no details and are
2119 !detailsVisible && !m_impl->annMemb; // rendered inside the group page or are not grouped at all
2120 if (writeAnchor)
2121 {
2122 QCString doxyArgs=argsString();
2123 QCString doxyName=name();
2124 if (!cname.isEmpty())
2125 {
2126 doxyName.prepend(cdname+getLanguageSpecificSeparator(getLanguage()));
2127 }
2128 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,anchor(),doxyName,doxyArgs);
2129 }
2130
2131 if (!detailsVisible)
2132 {
2133 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2134 ol.disable(OutputType::Man);
2135 ol.disable(OutputType::Latex);
2136 ol.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
2137 ol.docify("\n");
2138 ol.popGeneratorState();
2139 }
2140
2141 if (annoClassDef || m_impl->annMemb)
2142 {
2143 int j;
2144 for (j=0;j<indentLevel;j++)
2145 {
2146 ol.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
2147 }
2148 }
2149
2150 // *** write template lists
2151 if (m_impl->tArgList.hasParameters() && getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp)
2152 {
2153 if (!isAnonType) ol.startMemberTemplateParams();
2154 _writeTemplatePrefix(ol,d,m_impl->tArgList);
2155 if (!isAnonType) ol.endMemberTemplateParams(anchor(),inheritId);
2156 }
2157
2158
2159 // *** write type
2160 QCString ltype(m_impl->type);
2161 if (isTypedef() && getLanguage() != SrcLangExt_Slice)
2162 {
2163 ltype.prepend("typedef ");
2164 }
2165 if (isTypeAlias())
2166 {
2167 ltype="using";
2168 }
2169 // strip 'friend' keyword from ltype
2170 ltype.stripPrefix("friend ");
2171 static const reg::Ex r(R"(@\d+)");
2172 reg::Match match;
2173 std::string stype = ltype.str();
2174 bool endAnonScopeNeeded=FALSE;
2175 if (reg::search(stype,match,r)) // member has an anonymous type
2176 {
2177 int i = static_cast<int>(match.position());
2178 int l = static_cast<int>(match.length());
2179 //printf("annoClassDef=%p annMemb=%p scopeName='%s' anonymous='%s'\n",
2180 // annoClassDef,annMemb,qPrint(cname),qPrint(ltype.mid(i,l)));
2181
2182 if (annoClassDef) // type is an anonymous compound
2183 {
2184 int ir=i+l;
2185 //printf("<<<<<<<<<<<<<<\n");
2186 ol.startAnonTypeScope(indentLevel);
2187 annoClassDef->writeDeclaration(ol,m_impl->annMemb,inGroup,indentLevel+1,inheritedFrom,inheritId);
2188 //printf(">>>>>>>>>>>>>> startMemberItem(2)\n");
2189 anonType = OutputGenerator::MemberItemType::AnonymousEnd;
2190 ol.startMemberItem(anchor(),anonType,inheritId);
2191 int j;
2192 for (j=0;j< indentLevel;j++)
2193 {
2194 ol.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
2195 }
2196 QCString varName=ltype.right(ltype.length()-ir).stripWhiteSpace();
2197 //printf(">>>>>> ltype='%s' varName='%s'\n",qPrint(ltype),qPrint(varName));
2198 ol.docify("}");
2199 if (varName.isEmpty() && isAnonymous())
2200 {
2201 ol.docify(";");
2202 }
2203 else if (!varName.isEmpty() && (varName.at(0)=='*' || varName.at(0)=='&'))
2204 {
2205 ol.docify(" ");
2206 ol.docify(varName);
2207 }
2208 endAnonScopeNeeded=TRUE;
2209 }
2210 else
2211 {
2212 if (getAnonymousEnumType()) // type is an anonymous enum
2213 {
2214 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2215 d, // scope
2216 getBodyDef(), // fileScope
2217 this, // self
2218 ltype.left(i), // text
2219 FALSE // autoBreak
2220 );
2221 getAnonymousEnumType()->writeEnumDeclaration(ol,cd,nd,fd,gd);
2222 //ol+=*getAnonymousEnumType()->enumDecl();
2223 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,getFileDef(),this,ltype.right(ltype.length()-i-l),TRUE);
2224 }
2225 else
2226 {
2227 ltype = ltype.left(i) + " { ... } " + removeAnonymousScopes(ltype.right(ltype.length()-i-l));
2228 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2229 d, // scope
2230 getBodyDef(), // fileScope
2231 this, // self
2232 ltype, // text
2233 FALSE // autoBreak
2234 );
2235 }
2236 }
2237 }
2238 else if (ltype=="@") // rename type from enum values
2239 {
2240 ltype="";
2241 }
2242 else
2243 {
2244 if (isObjCMethod())
2245 {
2246 ltype.prepend("(");
2247 ltype.append(")");
2248 }
2249 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2250 d, // scope
2251 getBodyDef(), // fileScope
2252 this, // self
2253 ltype, // text
2254 FALSE // autoBreak
2255 );
2256 }
2257 bool htmlOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputType::Html);
2258 if (htmlOn && !ltype.isEmpty())
2259 {
2260 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
2261 }
2262 if (!ltype.isEmpty()) ol.docify(" ");
2263 if (htmlOn)
2264 {
2265 ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
2266 }
2267
2268 if (m_impl->annMemb)
2269 {
2270 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2271 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2272 ol.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
2273 ol.popGeneratorState();
2274 }
2275 else
2276 {
2277 ol.insertMemberAlign(m_impl->tArgList.hasParameters());
2278 }
2279
2280 // *** write name
2281 if (!isAnonymous()) // hide anonymous stuff
2282 {
2283 bool extractPrivateVirtual = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL);
2284 bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
2285 MemberDefMutable *annMemb = toMemberDefMutable(m_impl->annMemb);
2286 bool visibleIfPrivate = (protectionLevelVisible(protection()) ||
2287 m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Friend ||
2288 (m_impl->prot==Protection::Private &&
2289 (m_impl->virt!=Specifier::Normal || isOverride() || isFinal()) &&
2290 extractPrivateVirtual && hasDocumentation()
2291 ));
2292 //printf("Member name=`%s gd=%p md->groupDef=%p inGroup=%d isLinkable()=%d hasDocumentation=%d\n",qPrint(name()),gd,getGroupDef(),inGroup,isLinkable(),hasDocumentation());
2293 if (!name().isEmpty() && // name valid
2294 (hasDetailedDescription() || isReference()) && // has docs
2295 visibleIfPrivate &&
2296 !(isStatic() && getClassDef()==0 && !extractStatic) // hidden due to static-ness
2297 )
2298 {
2299 if (annMemb)
2300 {
2301 //printf("anchor=%s ann_anchor=%s\n",anchor(),annMemb->anchor());
2302 annMemb->writeLink(ol,
2303 annMemb->getClassDef(),
2304 annMemb->getNamespaceDef(),
2305 annMemb->getFileDef(),
2306 annMemb->getGroupDef());
2307 }
2308 else
2309 {
2310 //printf("writeLink %s->%d\n",qPrint(name),hasDocumentation());
2311 const ClassDef *rcd = cd;
2312 if (isReference() && getClassDef()) rcd = getClassDef();
2313 writeLink(ol,rcd,nd,fd,gd);
2314 }
2315 }
2316 else if (isDocumentedFriendClass())
2317 // if the member is an undocumented friend declaration for some class,
2318 // then maybe we can link to the class
2319 {
2320 writeLink(ol,getClass(name()),0,0,0);
2321 }
2322 else
2323 // there is a brief member description and brief member
2324 // descriptions are enabled or there is no detailed description.
2325 {
2326 const ClassDef *rcd = cd;
2327 if (isReference() && getClassDef()) rcd = getClassDef();
2328 writeLink(ol,rcd,nd,fd,gd,TRUE);
2329 }
2330 }
2331
2332 // *** write arguments
2333 if (!argsString().isEmpty() && !isObjCMethod())
2334 {
2335 if (!isDefine() && !isTypedef()) ol.writeString(" ");
2336 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
2337 d, // scope
2338 getBodyDef(), // fileScope
2339 this, // self
2340 isDefine() ?
2341 substitute(argsString(),",",", ") :
2342 isTypedef() ?
2343 substitute(argsString(),")(",") (") :
2344 argsString(), // text
2345 m_impl->annMemb, // autoBreak
2346 TRUE, // external
2347 FALSE, // keepSpaces
2348 indentLevel
2349 );
2350 }
2351 // *** write exceptions
2352 if (!excpString().isEmpty())
2353 {
2354 ol.writeString(" ");
2355 ol.docify(excpString());
2356 }
2357
2358 // *** write bitfields
2359 if (!m_impl->bitfields.isEmpty()) // add bitfields
2360 {
2361 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->bitfields);
2362 }
2363 else if (hasOneLineInitializer()
2364 //!init.isEmpty() && initLines==0 && // one line initializer
2365 //((maxInitLines>0 && userInitLines==-1) || userInitLines>0) // enabled by default or explicitly
2366 ) // add initializer
2367 {
2368 if (!isDefine())
2369 {
2370 //ol.writeString(" = ");
2371 ol.writeString(" ");
2372 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->initializer.simplifyWhiteSpace());
2373 }
2374 else
2375 {
2376 ol.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
2377 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->initializer);
2378 }
2379 }
2380 else if (isTypeAlias()) // using template alias
2381 {
2382 ol.writeString(" = ");
2383 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->type);
2384 }
2385
2386
2387 if ((isObjCMethod() || isObjCProperty()) && isImplementation())
2388 {
2389 ol.startTypewriter();
2390 ol.docify(" [implementation]");
2391 ol.endTypewriter();
2392 }
2393
2394 bool extractPrivate = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIVATE);
2395
2396 if (isProperty() && (isSettable() || isGettable() ||
2397 isPrivateSettable() || isPrivateGettable() ||
2398 isProtectedSettable() || isProtectedGettable()))
2399 {
2400 ol.writeLatexSpacing();
2401 ol.startTypewriter();
2402 ol.docify(" [");
2403 StringVector sl;
2404
2405 if (isGettable()) sl.push_back("get");
2406 if (isProtectedGettable()) sl.push_back("protected get");
2407 if (isSettable()) sl.push_back("set");
2408 if (isProtectedSettable()) sl.push_back("protected set");
2409 if (extractPrivate)
2410 {
2411 if (isPrivateGettable()) sl.push_back("private get");
2412 if (isPrivateSettable()) sl.push_back("private set");
2413 }
2414 bool first=true;
2415 for (const auto &s : sl)
2416 {
2417 if (!first)
2418 {
2419 ol.docify(", ");
2420 }
2421 first=false;
2422 ol.docify(s.c_str());
2423 }
2424 ol.docify("]");
2425 ol.endTypewriter();
2426 }
2427
2428 if (isEvent() && (isAddable() || isRemovable() || isRaisable()))
2429 {
2430 ol.writeLatexSpacing();
2431 ol.startTypewriter();
2432 ol.docify(" [");
2433 StringVector sl;
2434 if (isAddable()) sl.push_back("add");
2435 if (isRemovable()) sl.push_back("remove");
2436 if (isRaisable()) sl.push_back("raise");
2437 bool first=true;
2438 for (const auto &s : sl)
2439 {
2440 if (!first)
2441 {
2442 ol.docify(", ");
2443 }
2444 first=false;
2445 ol.docify(s.c_str());
2446 }
2447 ol.docify("]");
2448 ol.endTypewriter();
2449 }
2450
2451 if (writeAnchor)
2452 {
2453 ol.endDoxyAnchor(cfname,anchor());
2454 }
2455
2456 //printf("endMember %s annoClassDef=%p annEnumType=%p\n",
2457 // qPrint(name()),annoClassDef,annEnumType);
2458 ol.endMemberItem(anonType);
2459 if (endAnonScopeNeeded)
2460 {
2461 ol.endAnonTypeScope(indentLevel);
2462 }
2463
2464 // write brief description
2465 if (!briefDescription().isEmpty() &&
2466 Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC)
2467 )
2468 {
2469 auto parser { createDocParser() };
2470 auto ast { validatingParseDoc(*parser.get(),
2471 briefFile(),briefLine(),
2472 getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():d,
2473 this,briefDescription(),TRUE,FALSE,
2474 QCString(),TRUE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT)) };
2475 if (!ast->isEmpty())
2476 {
2477 ol.startMemberDescription(anchor(),inheritId);
2478 ol.writeDoc(ast.get(),getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():d,this);
2479 if (detailsVisible) // add More.. link only when both brief and details are visible
2480 {
2481 if (!isAnonymous()) // hide anonymous stuff
2482 {
2483 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2484 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
2485 ol.docify(" ");
2486 MemberDefMutable *annMemb = toMemberDefMutable(m_impl->annMemb);
2487 if (annMemb)
2488 {
2489 ol.startTextLink(annMemb->getOutputFileBase(),annMemb->anchor());
2490 ol.parseText(theTranslator->trMore());
2491 ol.endTextLink();
2492 }
2493 ol.popGeneratorState();
2494 }
2495 }
2496 // for RTF we need to add an extra empty paragraph
2497 ol.pushGeneratorState();
2498 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::RTF);
2499 ol.startParagraph();
2500 ol.endParagraph();
2501 ol.popGeneratorState();
2502 ol.endMemberDescription();
2503 }
2504 }
2505
2506 ol.endMemberDeclaration(anchor(),inheritId);
2507
2508 warnIfUndocumented();
2509 //printf("< %s MemberDefImpl::writeDeclaration() inGroup=%d\n",qPrint(qualifiedName()),inGroup);
2510}
2511
2512static std::mutex g_hasDetailedDescriptionMutex;
2513
2514bool MemberDefImpl::hasDetailedDescription() const
2515{
2516 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(g_hasDetailedDescriptionMutex);
2517 //printf(">hasDetailedDescription(cached=%d)\n",m_impl->hasDetailedDescriptionCached);
2518 if (!m_impl->hasDetailedDescriptionCached)
2519 {
2520 bool extractAll = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL);
2521 bool alwaysDetailedSec = Config_getBool(ALWAYS_DETAILED_SEC);
2522 bool repeatBrief = Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF);
2523 bool briefMemberDesc = Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC);
2524 bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
2525 bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
2526 bool extractPrivateVirtual = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIV_VIRTUAL);
2527 bool inlineSources = Config_getBool(INLINE_SOURCES);
2528
2529 // the member has detailed documentation because the user added some comments
2530 bool docFilter =
2531 // extract all is enabled
2532 extractAll ||
2533 // has detailed docs
2534 !documentation().isEmpty() ||
2535 // has inbody docs
2536 !inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty() ||
2537 // is an enum with values that are documented
2538 (isEnumerate() && hasDocumentedEnumValues()) ||
2539 // is documented enum value
2540 (m_impl->mtype==MemberType_EnumValue && !briefDescription().isEmpty()) ||
2541 // has brief description that is part of the detailed description
2542 (!briefDescription().isEmpty() && // has brief docs
2543 (alwaysDetailedSec && // they are visible in
2544 (repeatBrief || // detailed section or
2545 !briefMemberDesc // they are explicitly not
2546 ) // shown in brief section
2547 )
2548 ) ||
2549 // has one or more documented arguments
2550 (m_impl->templateMaster ?
2551 m_impl->templateMaster->argumentList().hasDocumentation() :
2552 m_impl->defArgList.hasDocumentation());
2553
2554 // generate function guard
2555 // ================== =======
2556 // _writeGroupInclude -> ignored in calculation
2557 // multiLineInitializer() -> hasMultiLineInitializer()
2558 // _writeReimplements -> _isReimplements()
2559 // _writeReimplementedBy -> _countReimplementedBy()>0
2560 // _writeExamples -> hasExamples()
2561 // _writeTypeConstraints -> m_impl->typeConstraints.hasParameters()
2562 // writeSourceDef -> !getSourceFileBase().isEmpty();
2563 // writeInlineCode -> INLINE_SOURCES && hasSources()
2564 // writeSourceRefs -> hasReferencesRelation() && hasSourceRefs()
2565 // writeSourceReffedBy -> hasReferencedByRelation() && hasSourceReffedBy()
2566 // _writeCallGraph -> _hasVisibleCallGraph()
2567 // _writeCallerGraph -> _hasVisibleCallerGraph()
2568
2569 // the member has detailed documentation because there is some generated info
2570 bool docInfo =
2571 // has a multi-line initialization block
2572 (hasMultiLineInitializer()) ||
2573 // reimplements / reimplemented by
2574 _isReimplements() || (_countReimplementedBy() > 0) ||
2575 // examples
2576 hasExamples() ||
2577 // type constraints
2578 m_impl->typeConstraints.hasParameters() ||
2579 // has source definition
2580 !getSourceFileBase().isEmpty() ||
2581 // has inline sources
2582 (inlineSources && hasSources()) ||
2583 // has references
2584 (hasReferencesRelation() && hasSourceRefs()) ||
2585 (hasReferencedByRelation() && hasSourceReffedBy()) ||
2586 // call graph
2587 _hasVisibleCallGraph() ||
2588 // caller graph
2589 _hasVisibleCallerGraph();
2590
2591 if (!hideUndocMembers) // if HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS is NO we also show the detailed section
2592 // if there is only some generated info
2593 {
2594 docFilter = docFilter || docInfo;
2595 }
2596
2597 // this is not a global static or global statics should be extracted
2598 bool staticFilter = getClassDef()!=0 || !isStatic() || extractStatic;
2599
2600 // only include members that are non-private unless EXTRACT_PRIVATE is
2601 // set to YES or the member is part of a group
2602 bool privateFilter = protectionLevelVisible(protection()) || m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Friend ||
2603 (m_impl->prot==Protection::Private && (m_impl->virt!=Specifier::Normal || isOverride() || isFinal()) && extractPrivateVirtual);
2604
2605 // hide friend (class|struct|union) member if HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS
2606 // is true
2607 bool friendCompoundFilter = !(Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS) && isFriend());
2608
2609 m_impl->detailedDescriptionCachedValue =
2610 (docFilter && staticFilter && privateFilter && friendCompoundFilter && !isHidden());
2611 //printf("docFilter=%d docInfo=%d staticFilter=%d privateFilter=%d friendCompoundFilter=%d !isHidden()=%d",
2612 // docFilter,docInfo,staticFilter,privateFilter,friendCompoundFilter,!isHidden());
2613 m_impl->hasDetailedDescriptionCached = true;
2614 }
2615 //printf("<hasDetailedDescription(cached=%d)\n",m_impl->hasDetailedDescriptionCached);
2616 return m_impl->detailedDescriptionCachedValue;
2617}
2618
2619bool MemberDefImpl::isDetailedSectionVisible(MemberListContainer container) const
2620{
2621 bool separateMemPages = Config_getBool(SEPARATE_MEMBER_PAGES);
2622 bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
2623 bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
2624 bool groupFilter = getGroupDef()==0 || container==MemberListContainer::Group || separateMemPages;
2625 bool fileFilter = getNamespaceDef()==0 || !getNamespaceDef()->isLinkable() || container!=MemberListContainer::File;
2626 bool simpleFilter = (hasBriefDescription() || !hideUndocMembers) && inlineSimpleStructs &&
2627 getClassDef()!=0 && getClassDef()->isSimple();
2628
2629 bool visible = hasDetailedDescription() && groupFilter && fileFilter &&
2630 !isReference();
2631 bool result = visible || simpleFilter;
2632 //printf("%s::isDetailedSectionVisible: %d groupFilter=%d fileFilter=%d\n",
2633 // qPrint(name()),result,groupFilter,fileFilter);
2634 return result;
2635}
2636
2637StringVector MemberDefImpl::getLabels(const Definition *container) const
2638{
2639 StringVector sl;
2640 bool inlineInfo = Config_getBool(INLINE_INFO);
2641
2642 Specifier lvirt=virtualness();
2643 if ((!isObjCMethod() || isOptional() || isRequired()) &&
2644 (protection()!=Protection::Public || lvirt!=Specifier::Normal ||
2645 isFriend() || isRelated() ||
2646 (isInline() && inlineInfo) ||
2647 isSignal() || isSlot() ||
2648 isStatic() || isExternal() ||
2649 (getClassDef() && getClassDef()!=container && container->definitionType()==TypeClass) ||
2650 (m_impl->memSpec & ~Entry::Inline)!=0
2651 )
2652 )
2653 {
2654 // write the member specifier list
2655 //ol.writeLatexSpacing();
2656 //ol.startTypewriter();
2657 //ol.docify(" [");
2658 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
2659 bool optVhdl = lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL;
2660 bool extractPrivate = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIVATE);
2661 if (optVhdl)
2662 {
2663 sl.push_back(theTranslator->trVhdlType(getMemberSpecifiers(),TRUE).str());
2664 }
2665 else
2666 {
2667 if (isFriend()) sl.push_back("friend");
2668 else if (isRelated()) sl.push_back("related");
2669 else
2670 {
2671 if (isExternal()) sl.push_back("extern");
2672 if (inlineInfo && isInline()) sl.push_back("inline");
2673 if (isExplicit()) sl.push_back("explicit");
2674 if (isMutable()) sl.push_back("mutable");
2675 if (isStatic()) sl.push_back("static");
2676 if (isGettable()) sl.push_back("get");
2677 if (isProtectedGettable()) sl.push_back("protected get");
2678 if (isSettable()) sl.push_back("set");
2679 if (isProtectedSettable()) sl.push_back("protected set");
2680 if (extractPrivate)
2681 {
2682 if (isPrivateGettable()) sl.push_back("private get");
2683 if (isPrivateSettable()) sl.push_back("private set");
2684 }
2685 if (isConstExpr()) sl.push_back("constexpr");
2686 if (isAddable()) sl.push_back("add");
2687 if (!isUNOProperty() && isRemovable()) sl.push_back("remove");
2688 if (isRaisable()) sl.push_back("raise");
2689 if (isReadable()) sl.push_back("read");
2690 if (isWritable()) sl.push_back("write");
2691 if (isFinal()) sl.push_back("final");
2692 if (isAbstract()) sl.push_back("abstract");
2693 if (isOverride()) sl.push_back("override");
2694 if (isInitonly()) sl.push_back("initonly");
2695 if (isSealed()) sl.push_back("sealed");
2696 if (isNew()) sl.push_back("new");
2697 if (isOptional()) sl.push_back("optional");
2698 if (isRequired()) sl.push_back("required");
2699
2700 if (isNonAtomic()) sl.push_back("nonatomic");
2701 else if (isObjCProperty()) sl.push_back("atomic");
2702
2703 // mutual exclusive Objective 2.0 property attributes
2704 if (isAssign()) sl.push_back("assign");
2705 else if (isCopy()) sl.push_back("copy");
2706 else if (isRetain()) sl.push_back("retain");
2707 else if (isWeak()) sl.push_back("weak");
2708 else if (lang!=SrcLangExt_CSharp && isStrong()) sl.push_back("strong");
2709 else if (isUnretained()) sl.push_back("unsafe_unretained");
2710
2711 if (!isObjCMethod())
2712 {
2713 if (protection()==Protection::Protected) sl.push_back("protected");
2714 else if (protection()==Protection::Private) sl.push_back("private");
2715 else if (protection()==Protection::Package) sl.push_back("package");
2716
2717 if (lvirt==Specifier::Virtual) sl.push_back("virtual");
2718 else if (lvirt==Specifier::Pure) sl.push_back("pure virtual");
2719 if (isSignal()) sl.push_back("signal");
2720 if (isSlot()) sl.push_back("slot");
2721 if (isDefault()) sl.push_back("default");
2722 if (isDelete()) sl.push_back("delete");
2723 if (isNoExcept()) sl.push_back("noexcept");
2724 if (isAttribute()) sl.push_back("attribute");
2725 if (isUNOProperty()) sl.push_back("property");
2726 if (isReadonly()) sl.push_back("readonly");
2727 if (isBound()) sl.push_back("bound");
2728 if (isUNOProperty() && isRemovable()) sl.push_back("removable");
2729 if (isConstrained()) sl.push_back("constrained");
2730 if (isTransient()) sl.push_back("transient");
2731 if (isMaybeVoid()) sl.push_back("maybevoid");
2732 if (isMaybeDefault()) sl.push_back("maybedefault");
2733 if (isMaybeAmbiguous()) sl.push_back("maybeambiguous");
2734 if (isPublished()) sl.push_back("published"); // enum
2735 }
2736 if (isObjCProperty() && isImplementation())
2737 {
2738 sl.push_back("implementation");
2739 }
2740 }
2741 if (getClassDef() &&
2742 container->definitionType()==TypeClass &&
2743 getClassDef()!=container &&
2744 !isRelated()
2745 )
2746 {
2747 sl.push_back("inherited");
2748 }
2749 }
2750 }
2751 else if (isObjCMethod() && isImplementation())
2752 {
2753 sl.push_back("implementation");
2754 }
2755
2756 for (const auto &sx : m_impl->qualifiers)
2757 {
2758 bool alreadyAdded = std::find(sl.begin(), sl.end(), sx) != sl.end();
2759 if (!alreadyAdded)
2760 {
2761 sl.push_back(sx);
2762 }
2763 }
2764
2765 return sl;
2766}

2813bool MemberDefImpl::_isReimplements() const
2814{
2815 const MemberDef *bmd=reimplements();
2816 const ClassDef *bcd=0;
2817 if (bmd && (bcd=bmd->getClassDef()))
2818 {
2819 // write class that contains a member that is reimplemented by this one
2820 if (bcd->isLinkable())
2821 {
2822 return true;
2823 }
2824 }
2825 return false;
2826}
2827void MemberDefImpl::_writeReimplements(OutputList &ol) const
2828{
2829 const MemberDef *bmd=reimplements();
2830 const ClassDef *bcd=0;
2831 if (bmd && (bcd=bmd->getClassDef()))
2832 {
2833 // write class that contains a member that is reimplemented by this one
2834 if (bcd->isLinkable())
2835 {
2836 ol.startParagraph();
2837 QCString reimplFromLine;
2838 if (bmd->virtualness()!=Specifier::Pure && bcd->compoundType()!=ClassDef::Interface)
2839 {
2840 reimplFromLine = theTranslator->trReimplementedFromList(1);
2841 }
2842 else
2843 {
2844 reimplFromLine = theTranslator->trImplementedFromList(1);
2845 }
2846 int markerPos = reimplFromLine.find("@0");
2847 if (markerPos!=-1) // should always pass this.
2848 {
2849 ol.parseText(reimplFromLine.left(markerPos)); //text left from marker
2850 if (bmd->isLinkable()) // replace marker with link
2851 {
2852 //Definition *bd=bmd->group;
2853 //if (bd==0) bd=bcd;
2854 ol.writeObjectLink(bmd->getReference(),bmd->getOutputFileBase(),
2855 bmd->anchor(),bcd->displayName());
2856
2857 //ol.writeObjectLink(bcd->getReference(),bcd->getOutputFileBase(),
2858 // bmd->anchor(),bcd->name());
2859 if ( bmd->isLinkableInProject() )
2860 {
2861 writePageRef(ol,bmd->getOutputFileBase(),bmd->anchor());
2862 }
2863 }
2864 else
2865 {
2866 ol.writeObjectLink(bcd->getReference(),bcd->getOutputFileBase(),
2867 QCString(),bcd->displayName());
2868 if (bcd->isLinkableInProject()/* && !Config_getBool(PDF_HYPERLINKS)*/ )
2869 {
2870 writePageRef(ol,bcd->getOutputFileBase(),bcd->anchor());
2871 }
2872 }
2873 ol.parseText(reimplFromLine.right(
2874 reimplFromLine.length()-markerPos-2)); // text right from marker
2875
2876 }
2877 else
2878 {
2879 err("translation error: no marker in trReimplementsFromList()\n");
2880 }
2881 ol.endParagraph();
2882 }
2883 }
2884}
2885
2886size_t MemberDefImpl::_countReimplementedBy() const
2887{
2888 const MemberVector &bml=reimplementedBy();
2889 size_t count=0;
2890 for (const auto &bmd : bml)
2891 {
2892 const ClassDef *bcd=bmd->getClassDef();
2893 // count the members that directly inherit from md and for
2894 // which the member and class are visible in the docs.
2895 if ( bcd && bmd->isLinkable() && bcd->isLinkable() )
2896 {
2897 count++;
2898 }
2899 }
2900 return count;
2901}
2902
2903void MemberDefImpl::_writeReimplementedBy(OutputList &ol) const
2904{
2905 const MemberVector &bml=reimplementedBy();
2906 size_t count = _countReimplementedBy();
2907 if (count>0)
2908 {
2909 auto replaceFunc = [&bml,&ol](size_t entryIndex)
2910 {
2911 size_t cnt=0;
2912 auto it = bml.begin();
2913 // find the entryIndex-th documented entry in the inheritance list.
2914 const MemberDef *bmd = 0;
2915 const ClassDef *bcd = 0;
2916 while (it!=bml.end())
2917 {
2918 bmd = *it;
2919 bcd = bmd->getClassDef();
2920 if ( bmd->isLinkable() && bcd->isLinkable())
2921 {
2922 if (cnt==entryIndex) break;
2923 cnt++;
2924 }
2925 ++it;
2926 }
2927
2928 if (bcd && bmd) // write link for marker
2929 {
2930 //ol.writeObjectLink(bcd->getReference(),bcd->getOutputFileBase(),
2931 // bmd->anchor(),bcd->name());
2932 ol.writeObjectLink(bmd->getReference(),bmd->getOutputFileBase(),
2933 bmd->anchor(),bcd->displayName());
2934
2935 if (bmd->isLinkableInProject() )
2936 {
2937 writePageRef(ol,bmd->getOutputFileBase(),bmd->anchor());
2938 }
2939 }
2940 };
2941
2942 QCString reimplInLine;
2943 if (m_impl->virt==Specifier::Pure || (getClassDef() && getClassDef()->compoundType()==ClassDef::Interface))
2944 {
2945 reimplInLine = theTranslator->trImplementedInList(static_cast<int>(count));
2946 }
2947 else
2948 {
2949 reimplInLine = theTranslator->trReimplementedInList(static_cast<int>(count));
2950 }
2951
2952 // write the list of classes that overwrite this member
2953 ol.startParagraph();
2954 writeMarkerList(ol,
2955 reimplInLine.str(),
2956 count,
2957 replaceFunc);
2958 ol.endParagraph();
2959 }
2960}
2961
2962void MemberDefImpl::_writeCategoryRelation(OutputList &ol) const
2963{
2964 if (getClassDef()) // this should be a member of a class/category
2965 {
2966 //printf("%s: category %s relation %s class=%s categoryOf=%s\n",
2967 // qPrint(name()),
2968 // m_impl->category ? qPrint(m_impl->category->name()) : "<none>",
2969 // m_impl->categoryRelation ? qPrint(m_impl->categoryRelation->name()) : "<none>",
2970 // qPrint(m_impl->classDef->name()),
2971 // m_impl->classDef->categoryOf() ? qPrint(m_impl->classDef->categoryOf()->name()) : "<none>"
2972 // );
2973 QCString text;
2974 QCString ref;
2975 QCString file;
2976 QCString anc;
2977 QCString name;
2978 int i=-1;
2979 if (m_impl->categoryRelation && m_impl->categoryRelation->isLinkable())
2980 {
2981 if (m_impl->category)
2982 {
2983 // this member is in a normal class and implements method categoryRelation from category
2984 // so link to method 'categoryRelation' with 'provided by category 'category' text.
2985 text = theTranslator->trProvidedByCategory();
2986 name = m_impl->category->displayName();
2987 }
2988 else if (getClassDef()->categoryOf())
2989 {
2990 // this member is part of a category so link to the corresponding class member of the class we extend
2991 // so link to method 'categoryRelation' with 'extends class 'classDef->categoryOf()'
2992 text = theTranslator->trExtendsClass();
2993 name = getClassDef()->categoryOf()->displayName();
2994 }
2995 i=text.find("@0");
2996 if (i!=-1)
2997 {
2998 const MemberDef *md = m_impl->categoryRelation;
2999 ref = md->getReference();
3000 file = md->getOutputFileBase();
3001 anc = md->anchor();
3002 }
3003 }
3004 if (i!=-1 && !name.isEmpty())
3005 {
3006 ol.startParagraph();
3007 ol.parseText(text.left(i));
3008 ol.writeObjectLink(ref,file,anc,name);
3009 ol.parseText(text.mid(i+2));
3010 ol.endParagraph();
3011 }
3012 }
3013}

3036void MemberDefImpl::_writeEnumValues(OutputList &ol,const Definition *container,
3037 const QCString &cfname,const QCString &ciname,
3038 const QCString &cname) const
3039{
3040 // For enum, we also write the documented enum values
3041 if (isEnumerate())
3042 {
3043 bool first=TRUE;
3044 //printf("** %s: enum values=%zu\n",qPrint(name()),enumFieldList().size());
3045 for (const auto &fmd : enumFieldList())
3046 {
3047 //printf("Enum %p: isLinkable()=%d\n",fmd,fmd->isLinkable());
3048 if (fmd->isLinkable())
3049 {
3050 if (first)
3051 {
3052 ol.startDescTable(theTranslator->trEnumerationValues());
3053 }
3054
3055 ol.startDescTableRow();
3056 ol.addIndexItem(fmd->name(),ciname);
3057 ol.addIndexItem(ciname,fmd->name());
3058
3059 ol.startDescTableTitle();
3060 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,fmd->anchor(),fmd->name(),fmd->argsString());
3061 first=FALSE;
3062 ol.docify(fmd->name());
3063 ol.disableAllBut(OutputType::Man);
3064 ol.writeString(" ");
3065 ol.enableAll();
3066 ol.endDoxyAnchor(cfname,fmd->anchor());
3067 ol.endDescTableTitle();
3068 ol.startDescTableData();
3069
3070 bool hasBrief = !fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty();
3071 bool hasDetails = !fmd->documentation().isEmpty();
3072
3073 if (hasBrief)
3074 {
3075 ol.generateDoc(fmd->briefFile(),fmd->briefLine(),
3076 getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():container,
3077 fmd,fmd->briefDescription(),TRUE,FALSE,
3078 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3079 }
3080 // FIXME:PARA
3081 //if (!fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty() &&
3082 // !fmd->documentation().isEmpty())
3083 //{
3084 // ol.newParagraph();
3085 //}
3086 if (hasDetails)
3087 {
3088 ol.generateDoc(fmd->docFile(),fmd->docLine(),
3089 getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():container,
3090 fmd,fmd->documentation()+"\n",TRUE,FALSE,
3091 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3092 }
3093 ol.endDescTableData();
3094 ol.endDescTableRow();
3095 }
3096 }
3097 if (!first)
3098 {
3099 ol.endDescTable();
3100 }
3101 }

3103
3104// match from the start of the scope until the last marker
3105static const reg::Ex reAnonymous(R"([\w:@]*@\d+)");
3106
3107QCString MemberDefImpl::displayDefinition() const
3108{
3109 QCString ldef = definition();
3110 QCString title = name();
3111 if (isEnumerate())
3112 {
3113 if (isAnonymous())
3114 {
3115 ldef = title = "anonymous enum";
3116 if (!m_impl->enumBaseType.isEmpty())
3117 {
3118 ldef+=" : "+m_impl->enumBaseType;
3119 }
3120 }
3121 else
3122 {
3123 ldef.prepend("enum ");
3124 if (isSliceLocal())
3125 {
3126 ldef.prepend("local ");
3127 }
3128 }
3129 }
3130 else if (isEnumValue())
3131 {
3132 if (isAnonymous())
3133 {
3134 ldef=ldef.mid(2);
3135 }
3136 }
3137
3138 std::string sdef = ldef.str();
3139 reg::Match match;
3140 if (reg::search(sdef,match,reAnonymous))
3141 {
3142 ldef = match.prefix().str() + " { ... } " + removeAnonymousScopes(match.suffix().str());
3143 }
3144
3145 const ClassDef *cd=getClassDef();
3146 if (cd && cd->isObjectiveC())
3147 {
3148 // strip scope name
3149 int ep = ldef.find("::");
3150 if (ep!=-1)
3151 {
3152 int sp=ldef.findRev(' ',ep);
3153 if (sp!=-1)
3154 {
3155 ldef=ldef.left(sp+1)+ldef.mid(ep+2);
3156 }
3157 }
3158 // strip keywords
3159 int dp = ldef.find(':');
3160 if (dp!=-1)
3161 {
3162 ldef=ldef.left(dp+1);
3163 }
3164 int l=ldef.length();
3165 //printf("start >%s<\n",qPrint(ldef));
3166 int i=l-1;
3167 while (i>=0 && (isId(ldef.at(i)) || ldef.at(i)==':')) i--;
3168 while (i>=0 && isspace(static_cast<uchar>(ldef.at(i)))) i--;
3169 if (i>0)
3170 {
3171 // insert branches around the type
3172 QCString tmp("("+ldef.left(i+1)+")"+ldef.mid(i+1));
3173 ldef=tmp;
3174 }
3175 //printf("end >%s< i=%d\n",qPrint(ldef),i);
3176 if (isStatic()) ldef.prepend("+ "); else ldef.prepend("- ");
3177 }
3178 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
3179 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
3180 return substitute(ldef,"::",sep);
3181}
3182
3183void MemberDefImpl::_writeGroupInclude(OutputList &ol,bool inGroup) const
3184{
3185 // only write out the include file if this is not part of a class or file
3186 // definition
3187 bool showGroupedMembInc = Config_getBool(SHOW_GROUPED_MEMB_INC);
3188 const FileDef *fd = getFileDef();
3189 QCString nm;
3190 if (fd) nm = getFileDef()->docName();
3191 if (inGroup && fd && showGroupedMembInc && !nm.isEmpty())
3192 {
3193 ol.startParagraph();
3194 ol.startTypewriter();
3195 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
3196 bool isIDLorJava = lang==SrcLangExt_IDL || lang==SrcLangExt_Java;
3197 if (isIDLorJava)
3198 {
3199 ol.docify("import ");
3200 }
3201 else
3202 {
3203 ol.docify("#include ");
3204 }
3205
3206 if (isIDLorJava) ol.docify("\""); else ol.docify("<");
3207
3208 if (fd->isLinkable())
3209 {
3210 ol.writeObjectLink(fd->getReference(),fd->getOutputFileBase(),fd->anchor(),nm);
3211 }
3212 else
3213 {
3214 ol.docify(nm);
3215 }
3216
3217 if (isIDLorJava) ol.docify("\""); else ol.docify(">");
3218
3219 ol.endTypewriter();
3220 ol.endParagraph();
3221 }
3222}

3224void MemberDefImpl::_writeMultiLineInitializer(OutputList &ol,const QCString &scopeName) const
3225{

3235 if (srcLangExt == SrcLangExt_Lex)
