3248
3249/*! Writes the "detailed documentation" section of this member to
3250 * all active output formats.
3251 */
3252void MemberDefImpl::writeDocumentation(const MemberList *ml,
3253 int memCount,int memTotal,
3254 OutputList &ol,
3255 const QCString &scName,
3256 const Definition *container,
3257 bool inGroup,
3258 bool showEnumValues,
3259 bool showInline
3260 ) const
3261{
3262 // if this member is in a group find the real scope name.
3263 bool hasParameterList = FALSE;
3264
3265 //printf("MemberDefImpl::writeDocumentation(): name='%s' hasDocs='%d' containerType=%d inGroup=%d sectionLinkable=%d\n",
3266 // qPrint(name()),hasDocs,container->definitionType(),inGroup,hasDetailedDescription());
3267
3268 //if ( !hasDocs ) return;
3269 //if (isEnumValue() && !showEnumValues) return;
3270
3271 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
3272 //printf("member=%s lang=%d\n",qPrint(name()),lang);
3273 bool optVhdl = lang==SrcLangExt_VHDL;
3274 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
3275
3276 QCString scopeName = scName;
3277 QCString memAnchor = anchor();
3278 QCString ciname = container->displayName();
3279 const Definition *scopedContainer = container; // see bug 753608
3280 if (container->definitionType()==TypeGroup)
3281 {
3282 if (getClassDef()) { scopeName=getClassDef()->displayName(); scopedContainer=getClassDef(); }
3283 else if (getNamespaceDef()) { scopeName=getNamespaceDef()->displayName(); scopedContainer=getNamespaceDef(); }
3284 else if (getFileDef()) { scopeName=getFileDef()->displayName(); scopedContainer=getFileDef(); }
3285 ciname = (toGroupDef(container))->groupTitle();
3286 }
3287 else if (container->definitionType()==TypeFile && getNamespaceDef() && getNamespaceDef()->isLinkable())
3288 { // member is in a namespace, but is written as part of the file documentation
3289 // as well, so we need to make sure its anchor is unique (it is not really used).
3290 memAnchor.prepend("file_");
3291 }
3292
3293 QCString cname = container->name();
3294 QCString cfname = getOutputFileBase();
3295
3296 // get member name
3297 QCString doxyName=name();
3298 // prepend scope if there is any. TODO: make this optional for C only docs
3299 if (!scopeName.isEmpty())
3300 {
3301 doxyName.prepend(scopeName+sep);
3302 }
3303 QCString doxyArgs=argsString();
3304
3305 QCString ldef = definition();
3306 QCString title = name();
3307 //printf("member '%s' def='%s'\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(ldef));
3308 if (isEnumerate())
3309 {
3310 if (title.at(0)=='@')
3311 {
3312 ldef = title = "anonymous enum";
3313 if (!m_impl->enumBaseType.isEmpty())
3314 {
3315 ldef+=" : "+m_impl->enumBaseType;
3316 }
3317 }
3318 else
3319 {
3320 if (lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp)
3321 {
3322 if (isEnumStruct()) ldef.prepend("struct ");
3323 else if (isStrong()) ldef.prepend("class ");
3324 }
3325 ldef.prepend("enum ");
3326 if (isSliceLocal())
3327 {
3328 ldef.prepend("local ");
3329 }
3330 }
3331 }
3332 else if (isEnumValue())
3333 {
3334 if (ldef.at(0)=='@')
3335 {
3336 ldef=ldef.mid(2);
3337 }
3338 }
3339 else if (isFunction() && !isObjCMethod())
3340 {
3341 title += "()";
3342 }
3343 if (lang == SrcLangExt_Slice)
3344 {
3345 // Remove the container scope from the member name.
3346 QCString prefix = scName + sep;
3347 int pos = ldef.findRev(prefix.data());
3348 if(pos != -1)
3349 {
3350 ldef.remove(pos, prefix.length());
3351 }
3352 }
3353
3354 //----------------------------------------
3355
3356 ol.pushGeneratorState();
3357
3358 bool htmlEndLabelTable=FALSE;
3359 StringVector sl = getLabels(scopedContainer);
3360
3361 static const reg::Ex r(R"(@\d+)");
3362 reg::Match match;
3363 std::string sdef = ldef.str();
3364 if ((isVariable() || isTypedef()) && reg::search(sdef,match,r))
3365 {
3366 // find enum type and insert it in the definition
3367 bool found=false;
3368 for (const auto &vmd : *ml)
3369 {
3370 if (vmd->isEnumerate() && match.str()==vmd->name())
3371 {
3372 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,memAnchor,doxyName,doxyArgs);
3373 ol.startMemberDoc(ciname,name(),memAnchor,name(),memCount,memTotal,showInline);
3374 std::string prefix = match.prefix().str();
3375 std::string suffix = match.suffix().str();
3376 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,prefix.c_str());
3377 vmd->writeEnumDeclaration(ol,getClassDef(),getNamespaceDef(),getFileDef(),getGroupDef());
3378 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,suffix.c_str());
3379
3380 found=true;
3381 break;
3382 }
3383 }
3384 if (!found) // anonymous compound
3385 {
3386 ClassDef *annoClassDef=getClassDefOfAnonymousType();
3387 QCString typeName;
3388 if (annoClassDef) typeName=annoClassDef->compoundTypeString();
3389 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,memAnchor,doxyName,doxyArgs);
3390 ol.startMemberDoc(ciname,name(),memAnchor,"["+typeName+"]",memCount,memTotal,showInline);
3391 // search for the last anonymous compound name in the definition
3392
3393 ol.startMemberDocName(isObjCMethod());
3394 if (reg::search(sdef,match,reAnonymous))
3395 {
3396 std::string prefix = match.prefix().str();
3397 std::string suffix = match.suffix().str();
3398 ol.docify(prefix.c_str());
3399 ol.docify(" { ... } ");
3400 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,removeAnonymousScopes(suffix.c_str()));
3401 }
3402 else
3403 {
3404 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,ldef);
3405 }
3406 }
3407 }
3408 else // not an enum value or anonymous compound
3409 {
3410 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,memAnchor,doxyName,doxyArgs);
3411 ol.startMemberDoc(ciname,name(),memAnchor,title,memCount,memTotal,showInline);
3412
3413 if (!m_impl->metaData.isEmpty() && getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Slice)
3414 {
3415 ol.startMemberDocPrefixItem();
3416 ol.docify(m_impl->metaData);
3417 ol.endMemberDocPrefixItem();
3418 }
3419
3420 const ClassDef *cd=getClassDef();
3421 const NamespaceDef *nd=getNamespaceDef();
3422 if (!Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
3423 {
3424 bool first=TRUE;
3425 if (!m_impl->defTmpArgLists.empty() && lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp)
3426 // definition has explicit template parameter declarations
3427 {
3428 for (const ArgumentList &tal : m_impl->defTmpArgLists)
3429 {
3430 if (!tal.empty())
3431 {
3432 if (!first) ol.docify(" ");
3433 ol.startMemberDocPrefixItem();
3434 _writeTemplatePrefix(ol,scopedContainer,tal);
3435 ol.endMemberDocPrefixItem();
3436 }
3437 }
3438 }
3439 else // definition gets it template parameters from its class
3440 // (since no definition was found)
3441 {
3442 if (cd && lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp && !isTemplateSpecialization())
3443 {
3444 for (const ArgumentList &tal : cd->getTemplateParameterLists())
3445 {
3446 if (!tal.empty())
3447 {
3448 if (!first) ol.docify(" ");
3449 ol.startMemberDocPrefixItem();
3450 _writeTemplatePrefix(ol,scopedContainer,tal,false);
3451 ol.endMemberDocPrefixItem();
3452 }
3453 }
3454 }
3455 if (m_impl->tArgList.hasParameters() && lang==SrcLangExt_Cpp) // function template prefix
3456 {
3457 ol.startMemberDocPrefixItem();
3458 _writeTemplatePrefix(ol,scopedContainer,m_impl->tArgList);
3459 ol.endMemberDocPrefixItem();
3460 }
3461 }
3462 }
3463
3464 if (!sl.empty())
3465 {
3466 ol.pushGeneratorState();
3467 ol.disableAll();
3468 ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
3469 ol.writeString("<table class=\"mlabels\">\n");
3470 ol.writeString(" <tr>\n");
3471 ol.writeString(" <td class=\"mlabels-left\">\n");
3472 ol.popGeneratorState();
3473 htmlEndLabelTable=TRUE;
3474 }
3475
3476 ol.startMemberDocName(isObjCMethod());
3477 if (cd && cd->isObjectiveC())
3478 {
3479 // strip scope name
3480 int ep = ldef.find("::");
3481 if (ep!=-1)
3482 {
3483 int sp=ldef.findRev(' ',ep);
3484 if (sp!=-1)
3485 {
3486 ldef=ldef.left(sp+1)+ldef.mid(ep+2);
3487 } else {
3488 ldef=ldef.mid(ep+2);
3489 }
3490 }
3491 // strip keywords
3492 int dp = ldef.find(':');
3493 if (dp!=-1)
3494 {
3495 ldef=ldef.left(dp+1);
3496 }
3497 int dl=ldef.length();
3498 //printf("start >%s<\n",qPrint(ldef));
3499 int i=dl-1;
3500 while (i>=0 && (isId(ldef.at(i)) || ldef.at(i)==':')) i--;
3501 while (i>=0 && isspace(static_cast<uchar>(ldef.at(i)))) i--;
3502 if (i>0)
3503 {
3504 // insert branches around the type
3505 QCString tmp("("+ldef.left(i+1)+")"+ldef.mid(i+1));
3506 ldef=tmp;
3507 }
3508 //printf("end >%s< i=%d\n",qPrint(ldef),i);
3509 if (isStatic()) ldef.prepend("+ "); else ldef.prepend("- ");
3510 }
3511
3512 if (optVhdl)
3513 {
3514 hasParameterList=VhdlDocGen::writeVHDLTypeDocumentation(this,scopedContainer,ol);
3515 }
3516 else if (lang==SrcLangExt_Slice)
3517 {
3518 // Eliminate the self-reference.
3519 int pos = ldef.findRev(' ');
3520 if (pos<0) pos=0;
3521 if (pos>0)
3522 {
3523 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),
3524 scopedContainer,
3525 getBodyDef(),
3526 this,
3527 ldef.left(pos)
3528 );
3529 }
3530 ol.docify(ldef.mid(pos));
3531 const Definition *scope = cd;
3532 if (scope==0) scope = nd;
3533 hasParameterList=writeDefArgumentList(ol,scope,this);
3534 }
3535 else
3536 {
3537 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),
3538 scopedContainer,
3539 getBodyDef(),
3540 this,
3541 substitute(ldef,"::",sep)
3542 );
3543 const Definition *scope = cd;
3544 if (scope==0) scope = nd;
3545 hasParameterList=writeDefArgumentList(ol,scope,this);
3546 }
3547
3548 if (hasOneLineInitializer()) // add initializer
3549 {
3550 if (!isDefine())
3551 {
3552 //ol.docify(" = ");
3553 ol.docify(" ");
3554 QCString init = m_impl->initializer.simplifyWhiteSpace();
3555 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,init);
3556 }
3557 else
3558 {
3559 ol.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
3560 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scopedContainer,getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->initializer);
3561 }
3562 }
3563 if (!excpString().isEmpty()) // add exception list
3564 {
3565 writeExceptionList(ol,cd,this);
3566 hasParameterList=true; // call endParameterList below
3567 }
3568 }
3569
3570 ol.pushGeneratorState();
3571 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
3572 if (!sl.empty())
3573 {
3574 ol.startLabels();
3575 size_t count=0;
3576 for (const auto &s : sl)
3577 {
3578 count++;
3579 ol.writeLabel(s.c_str(),count==sl.size());
3580 }
3581 ol.endLabels();
3582 }
3583 ol.popGeneratorState();
3584
3585 if (hasParameterList)
3586 {
3587 ol.endParameterList();
3588 ol.endMemberDoc(TRUE);
3589 }
3590 else
3591 {
3592 ol.endMemberDocName();
3593 ol.endMemberDoc(FALSE);
3594 }
3595
3596 // for HTML write the labels here
3597 ol.pushGeneratorState();
3598 ol.disableAll();
3599 ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
3600 if (htmlEndLabelTable)
3601 {
3602 ol.writeString(" </td>\n");
3603 ol.writeString(" <td class=\"mlabels-right\">\n");
3604 ol.startLabels();
3605 size_t count=0;
3606 for (const auto &s : sl)
3607 {
3608 count++;
3609 ol.writeLabel(s.c_str(),count==sl.size());
3610 }
3611 ol.endLabels();
3612 ol.writeString(" </td>\n");
3613 ol.writeString(" </tr>\n");
3614 ol.writeString("</table>\n");
3615 }
3616 ol.writeString("</div>");
3617 ol.popGeneratorState();
3618
3619
3620 ol.endDoxyAnchor(cfname,memAnchor);
3621 ol.startIndent();
3622
3623 _writeGroupInclude(ol,inGroup);
3624
3625 /* write multi-line initializer (if any) */
3626 if (hasMultiLineInitializer()) _writeMultiLineInitializer(ol,scopeName);
3627
3628 /* write brief description */
3629 QCString brief = briefDescription();
3630 if (!brief.isEmpty() &&
3631 (Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF) ||
3632 !Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC)
3633 )
3634 )
3635 {
3636 ol.startParagraph();
3637 ol.generateDoc(briefFile(),briefLine(),
3638 scopedContainer,this,
3639 brief,FALSE,FALSE,
3640 QCString(),TRUE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3641 ol.endParagraph();
3642 }
3643
3644 /* write detailed description */
3645 QCString detailed = documentation();
3646 if (!detailed.isEmpty() ||
3647 !inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
3648 {
3649 // write vhdl inline code with or without option INLINE_SOURCE
3650 if (optVhdl && VhdlDocGen::isMisc(this))
3651 {
3652 VhdlDocGen::writeSource(this,ol,cname);
3653 return;
3654 }
3655 else
3656 {
3657 ol.generateDoc(docFile(),docLine(),scopedContainer,this,detailed+"\n",TRUE,FALSE,
3658 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3659 }
3660
3661 if (!inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
3662 {
3663 ol.generateDoc(inbodyFile(),inbodyLine(),
3664 scopedContainer,this,
3665 inbodyDocumentation()+"\n",TRUE,FALSE,
3666 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3667 }
3668 }
3669 else if (!brief.isEmpty() && (Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF) || !Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC)))
3670 {
3671 if (!inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
3672 {
3673 ol.generateDoc(inbodyFile(),inbodyLine(),scopedContainer,this,inbodyDocumentation()+"\n",TRUE,FALSE,
3674 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3675 }
3676 }
3677
3678
3679 //printf("***** defArgList=%p name=%s docs=%s hasDocs=%d\n",
3680 // defArgList,
3681 // defArgList?defArgList->hasDocumentation():-1);
3682 const ArgumentList &docArgList = m_impl->templateMaster ?
3683 m_impl->templateMaster->argumentList() :
3684 m_impl->defArgList;
3685 if (docArgList.hasDocumentation())
3686 {
3687 QCString paramDocs;
3688 for (const Argument &a : docArgList)
3689 {
3690 if (a.hasDocumentation())
3691 {
3692 QCString docsWithoutDir = a.docs;
3693 QCString direction = extractDirection(docsWithoutDir);
3694 paramDocs+="@param"+direction+" "+a.name+" "+docsWithoutDir;
3695 }
3696 }
3697 // feed the result to the documentation parser
3698 ol.generateDoc(
3699 docFile(),docLine(),
3700 scopedContainer,
3701 this, // memberDef
3702 paramDocs, // docStr
3703 TRUE, // indexWords
3704 FALSE, // isExample
3705 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT)
3706 );
3707
3708 }
3709
3710 _writeEnumValues(ol,scopedContainer,cfname,ciname,cname);
3711 _writeReimplements(ol);
3712 _writeReimplementedBy(ol);
3713 _writeCategoryRelation(ol);
3714 _writeExamples(ol);
3715 _writeTypeConstraints(ol);
3716 writeSourceDef(ol,cname);
3717 writeInlineCode(ol,cname);
3718 if (hasReferencesRelation()) writeSourceRefs(ol,cname);
3719 if (hasReferencedByRelation()) writeSourceReffedBy(ol,cname);
3720 _writeCallGraph(ol);
3721 _writeCallerGraph(ol);
3722
3723 ol.endIndent();
3724
3725 // enable LaTeX again
3726 //if (Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL) && !hasDocs) ol.enable(OutputType::Latex);
3727 ol.popGeneratorState();
3728
3729 warnIfUndocumentedParams();
3730}
3731
3732// strip scope and field name from the type
3733// example: "struct N<K::J>::S.v.c" will become "struct v"
3734static QCString simplifyTypeForTable(const QCString &s)
3735{
3736 QCString ts=removeAnonymousScopes(s);
3737 if (ts.endsWith("::")) ts = ts.left(ts.length()-2);
3738 static const reg::Ex re1(R"(\a\w*::)"); // non-template version
3739 static const reg::Ex re2(R"(\a\w*<[^>]*>::)"); // template version
3740 reg::Match match;
3741 std::string t = ts.str();
3742 while (reg::search(t,match,re2) || reg::search(t,match,re1))
3743 {
3744 t = match.prefix().str() + match.suffix().str(); // remove the matched part
3745 }
3746 //printf("simplifyTypeForTable(%s)->%s\n",qPrint(s),t.c_str());
3747 return QCString(t);
3748}
3749
3750QCString MemberDefImpl::fieldType() const
3751{
3752 QCString type = m_impl->accessorType;
3753 if (type.isEmpty())
3754 {
3755 type = m_impl->type;
3756 }
3757
3758 if (isTypedef() && getLanguage() != SrcLangExt_Slice) type.prepend("typedef ");
3759 return simplifyTypeForTable(type);
3760}
3761
3762void MemberDefImpl::writeMemberDocSimple(OutputList &ol, const Definition *container) const
3763{
3764 Definition *scope = getOuterScope();
3765 QCString doxyName = name();
3766 QCString doxyArgs = argsString();
3767 QCString memAnchor = anchor();
3768 QCString cfname = getOutputFileBase();
3769 QCString cname;
3770 if (scope) cname = scope->name();
3771 if (doxyName.at(0)=='@')
3772 {
3773 doxyName="__unnamed__";
3774 }
3775
3776 ClassDef *cd = m_impl->accessorClass;
3777 //printf("===> %s::anonymous: %s\n",qPrint(name()),cd?qPrint(cd->name()):"<none>");
3778
3779 if (container && container->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass &&
3780 !(toClassDef(container))->isJavaEnum())
3781 {
3782 ol.startInlineMemberType();
3783 ol.startDoxyAnchor(cfname,cname,memAnchor,doxyName,doxyArgs);
3784
3785 QCString ts = fieldType();
3786
3787 if (cd) // cd points to an anonymous struct pointed to by this member
3788 // so we add a link to it from the type column.
3789 {
3790 int i=0;
3791 const char *prefixes[] = { "struct ","union ","class ", 0 };
3792 const char **p = prefixes;
3793 while (*p)
3794 {
3795 int l=qstrlen(*p);
3796 if (ts.left(l)==*p)
3797 {
3798 ol.writeString(*p);
3799 i=l;
3800 }
3801 p++;
3802 }
3803 ol.writeObjectLink(cd->getReference(),
3804 cd->getOutputFileBase(),
3805 cd->anchor(),ts.mid(i));
3806 }
3807 else // use standard auto linking
3808 {
3809 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
3810 scope, // scope
3811 getBodyDef(), // fileScope
3812 this, // self
3813 ts // text
3814 );
3815 }
3816 ol.endDoxyAnchor(cfname,memAnchor);
3817 ol.endInlineMemberType();
3818 }
3819
3820 ol.startInlineMemberName();
3821 ol.docify(doxyName);
3822 if (isVariable() && !argsString().isEmpty() && !isObjCMethod())
3823 {
3824 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),getOuterScope(),getBodyDef(),this,argsString());
3825 }
3826 if (!m_impl->bitfields.isEmpty()) // add bitfields
3827 {
3828 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),getOuterScope(),getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->bitfields);
3829 }
3830 if (hasOneLineInitializer() && !isDefine())
3831 {
3832 ol.writeString(" ");
3833 linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),getOuterScope(),getBodyDef(),this,m_impl->initializer.simplifyWhiteSpace());
3834 }
3835 ol.endInlineMemberName();
3836
3837 ol.startInlineMemberDoc();
3838
3839 QCString brief = briefDescription();
3840 QCString detailed = documentation();
3841
3842 /* write brief description */
3843 if (!brief.isEmpty())
3844 {
3845 ol.generateDoc(briefFile(),briefLine(),
3846 getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():container,this,
3847 brief,FALSE,FALSE,
3848 QCString(),TRUE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3849 }
3850
3851 /* write detailed description */
3852 if (!detailed.isEmpty())
3853 {
3854 if (!brief.isEmpty())
3855 {
3856 ol.disable(OutputType::Html);
3857 ol.lineBreak();
3858 ol.enable(OutputType::Html);
3859 }
3860 ol.generateDoc(docFile(),docLine(),
3861 getOuterScope()?getOuterScope():container,this,
3862 detailed+"\n",FALSE,FALSE,
3863 QCString(),FALSE,FALSE,Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT));
3864
3865 }
3866
3867 ol.endInlineMemberDoc();
3868}
3869
3870QCString MemberDefImpl::memberTypeName() const
3871{
3872 switch (m_impl->mtype)
3873 {
3874 case MemberType_Define: return "macro definition";
3875 case MemberType_Function: return "function";
3876 case MemberType_Variable: return "variable";
3877 case MemberType_Typedef: return "typedef";
3878 case MemberType_Enumeration: return "enumeration";
3879 case MemberType_EnumValue: return "enumvalue";
3880 case MemberType_Signal: return "signal";
3881 case MemberType_Slot: return "slot";
3882 case MemberType_Friend: return "friend";
3883 case MemberType_DCOP: return "dcop";
3884 case MemberType_Property: return "property";
3885 case MemberType_Event: return "event";
3886 case MemberType_Interface: return "interface";
3887 case MemberType_Service: return "service";
3888 case MemberType_Sequence: return "sequence";
3889 case MemberType_Dictionary: return "dictionary";
3890 default: return "unknown";
3891 }
3892}
3893
3894void MemberDefImpl::warnIfUndocumented() const
3895{
3896 /*
3897 * Removed bug_303020:
3898 * if (m_impl->memberGroup) return;
3899 */
3900 const ClassDef *cd = getClassDef();
3901 const NamespaceDef *nd = getNamespaceDef();
3902 const FileDef *fd = getFileDef();
3903 const GroupDef *gd = getGroupDef();
3904 const Definition *d=0;
3905 QCString t;
3906 if (cd)
3907 t=cd->compoundTypeString(), d=cd;
3908 else if (nd)
3909 {
3910 d=nd;
3911 t=nd->compoundTypeString();
3912 }
3913 else if (gd)
3914 t="group", d=gd;
3915 else
3916 t="file", d=fd;
3917 bool extractAll = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL);
3918
3919 //printf("%s:warnIfUndoc: hasUserDocs=%d isFriendClass=%d protection=%d isRef=%d isDel=%d\n",
3920 // qPrint(name()),
3921 // hasUserDocumentation(),isFriendClass(),protectionLevelVisible(m_impl->prot),isReference(),isDeleted());
3922 if ((!hasUserDocumentation() && !extractAll) &&
3923 !isFriendClass() &&
3924 name().find('@')==-1 && d && d->name().find('@')==-1 &&
3925 protectionLevelVisible(m_impl->prot) &&
3926 !isReference() && !isDeleted()
3927 )
3928 {
3929 warn_undoc(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),"Member %s%s (%s) of %s %s is not documented.",
3930 qPrint(name()),qPrint(argsString()),qPrint(memberTypeName()),qPrint(t),qPrint(d->name()));
3931 }
3932 else if (!hasDetailedDescription())
3933 {
3934 warnIfUndocumentedParams();
3935 }
3936
3937 // if it is an enum, we check that its members are documented
3938 if (!extractAll && isEnumerate() && Config_getBool(WARN_IF_UNDOC_ENUM_VAL))
3939 {
3940 for (const auto &fmd : enumFieldList())
3941 {
3942 if (!fmd->isLinkableInProject())
3943 {
3944 warn(fmd->getDefFileName(),fmd->getDefLine(), "Documentation for enum member '%s::%s' is missing.",
3945 qPrint(qualifiedName()), qPrint(fmd->name()));
3946 }
3947 }
3948 }
3949}
3950
3951bool MemberDefImpl::visibleInIndex() const
3952{
3953 bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
3954 bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
3955 return (!isAnonymous() &&
3956 (!hideUndocMembers || hasDocumentation()) &&
3957 (!isStatic() || extractStatic) &&
3958 isLinkable()
3959 );
3960}
3961
3962static QCString stripTrailingReturn(const QCString &trailRet)
3963{
3964 QCString ret = trailRet;
3965
3966 ret = ret.stripWhiteSpace();
3967 if (ret.startsWith("->"))
3968 {
3969 ret = ret.mid(2).stripWhiteSpace();
3970 return ret;
3971 }
3972 return trailRet;
3973}
3974
3975static std::mutex g_detectUndocumentedParamsMutex;
3976
3977void MemberDefImpl::detectUndocumentedParams(bool hasParamCommand,bool hasReturnCommand) const
3978{
3979 // this function is called while parsing the documentation. A member can have multiple
3980 // documentation blocks, which could be handled by multiple threads, hence this guard.
3981 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(g_detectUndocumentedParamsMutex);
3982
3983 bool isPython = getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Python;
3984
3985 if (!m_impl->hasDocumentedParams && hasParamCommand)
3986 {
3987 //printf("%s:hasDocumentedParams=TRUE;\n",qPrint(name()));
3988 m_impl->hasDocumentedParams = TRUE;
3989 }
3990 else if (!m_impl->hasDocumentedParams)
3991 {
3992 const ArgumentList &al = argumentList();
3993 const ArgumentList &declAl = declArgumentList();
3994 bool allDoc=TRUE; // no parameter => all parameters are documented
3995 if ( // member has parameters
3996 al.hasParameters() // with at least one parameter (that is not void)
3997 )
3998 {
3999 // see if all parameters have documentation
4000 for (auto it = al.begin(); it!=al.end() && allDoc; ++it)
4001 {
4002 Argument a = *it;
4003 if (!a.name.isEmpty() && a.type!="void" &&
4004 !(isPython && (a.name=="self" || a.name=="cls"))
4005 )
4006 {
4007 allDoc = !a.docs.isEmpty();
4008 }
4009 //printf("a->type=%s a->name=%s doc=%s\n",
4010 // qPrint(a->type),qPrint(a->name),qPrint(a->docs));
4011 }
4012 if (!allDoc && declAl.empty()) // try declaration arguments as well
4013 {
4014 allDoc=TRUE;
4015 for (auto it = al.begin(); it!=al.end() && allDoc; ++it)
4016 {
4017 Argument a = *it;
4018 if (!a.name.isEmpty() && a.type!="void" &&
4019 !(isPython && (a.name=="self" || a.name=="cls"))
4020 )
4021 {
4022 allDoc = !a.docs.isEmpty();
4023 }
4024 //printf("a->name=%s doc=%s\n",qPrint(a->name),qPrint(a->docs));
4025 }
4026 }
4027 }
4028 if (allDoc)
4029 {
4030 //printf("%s:hasDocumentedParams=TRUE;\n",qPrint(name()));
4031 m_impl->hasDocumentedParams = TRUE;
4032 }
4033 }
4034
4035 //printf("Member %s hasDocumentedReturnType=%d hasReturnCommand=%d\n",
4036 // qPrint(name()),m_impl->hasDocumentedReturnType,hasReturnCommand);
4037 if (!m_impl->hasDocumentedReturnType && // docs not yet found
4038 hasReturnCommand)
4039 {
4040 m_impl->hasDocumentedReturnType = TRUE;
4041 }
4042}
4043
4044void MemberDefImpl::warnIfUndocumentedParams() const
4045{
4046 QCString returnType = typeString();
4047 bool isFortran = getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Fortran;
4048 bool isFortranSubroutine = isFortran && returnType.find("subroutine")!=-1;
4049
4050 bool isVoidReturn = (returnType=="void") || (returnType.endsWith(" void"));
4051 if (!isVoidReturn && returnType == "auto")
4052 {
4053 const ArgumentList &defArgList=isDocsForDefinition() ? argumentList() : declArgumentList();
4054 if (!defArgList.trailingReturnType().isEmpty())
4055 {
4056 QCString strippedTrailingReturn = stripTrailingReturn(defArgList.trailingReturnType());
4057 isVoidReturn = (strippedTrailingReturn=="void") || (strippedTrailingReturn.endsWith(" void"));
4058 }
4059 }
4060 if (!Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL) &&
4061 Config_getBool(WARN_IF_UNDOCUMENTED) &&
4062 Config_getBool(WARN_NO_PARAMDOC) &&
4063 isFunction() &&
4064 !isDeleted() &&
4065 !isReference() &&
4066 !Doxygen::suppressDocWarnings)
4067 {
4068 if (!m_impl->hasDocumentedParams)
4069 {
4070 warn_doc_error(docFile(),docLine(),
4071 "parameters of member %s are not documented",
4072 qPrint(qualifiedName()));
4073 }
4074 if (!m_impl->hasDocumentedReturnType &&
4075 hasDocumentation() && !returnType.isEmpty() &&
4076 !( // not one of the cases where nothing is returned
4077 isVoidReturn || // void return type
4078 isFortranSubroutine || // fortran subroutine
4079 isConstructor() || // a constructor
4080 isDestructor() // or destructor
4081 )
4082 )
4083 {
4084 warn_doc_error(docFile(),docLine(),
4085 "return type of member %s is not documented",
4086 qPrint(qualifiedName()));
4087 }
4088 }
4089 if (Config_getBool(WARN_IF_DOC_ERROR) &&
4090 m_impl->hasDocumentedReturnType &&
4091 (isVoidReturn || // void return type
4092 isFortranSubroutine || // fortran subroutine
4093 isConstructor() || // a constructor
4094 isDestructor())) // or destructor
4095 {
4096 warn_doc_error(docFile(),docLine(),"found documented return type for %s that does not return anything",
4097 qPrint(qualifiedName()));
4098 }
4099}

4101bool MemberDefImpl::isDocumentedFriendClass() const
4102{
4103 ClassDef *fcd=0;
4104 QCString baseName=name();
4105 int i=baseName.find('<');
4106 if (i!=-1) baseName=baseName.left(i);
4107 return (isFriendClass() &&
4108 (fcd=getClass(baseName)) && fcd->isLinkable());
4109}

4136
4137void MemberDefImpl::setAnchor()
4138{
4139 QCString memAnchor = name();
4140 if (!m_impl->args.isEmpty()) memAnchor+=m_impl->args;
4141
4142 memAnchor.prepend(definition()); // actually the method name is now included
4143 // twice, which is silly, but we keep it this way for backward
4144 // compatibility.
4145
4146 // include number of template arguments as well,
4147 // to distinguish between two template
4148 // specializations that only differ in the template parameters.
4149 if (m_impl->tArgList.hasParameters())
4150 {
4151 char buf[20];
4152 qsnprintf(buf,20,"%d:",static_cast<int>(m_impl->tArgList.size()));
4153 buf[19]='\0';
4154 memAnchor.prepend(buf);
4155 }
4156 if (!m_impl->requiresClause.isEmpty())
4157 {
4158 memAnchor+=" "+m_impl->requiresClause;
4159 }
4160
4161 // convert to md5 hash
4162 uchar md5_sig[16];
4163 char sigStr[33];
4164 MD5Buffer(memAnchor.data(),memAnchor.length(),md5_sig);
4165 MD5SigToString(md5_sig,sigStr);
4166 m_impl->anc = QCString("a")+sigStr;
4167}

4211
4212MemberDefMutable *MemberDefImpl::createTemplateInstanceMember(
4213 const ArgumentList &formalArgs,const std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> &actualArgs) const
4214{
4215 //printf(" Member %s %s %s\n",typeString(),qPrint(name()),argsString());
4216 std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> actualArgList = std::make_unique<ArgumentList>(m_impl->defArgList);
4217 if (!m_impl->defArgList.empty())
4218 {
4219 // replace formal arguments with actuals
4220 for (Argument &arg : *actualArgList)
4221 {
4222 arg.type = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(arg.type,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4223 }
4224 actualArgList->setTrailingReturnType(
4225 substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(actualArgList->trailingReturnType(),formalArgs,actualArgs));
4226 }
4227
4228 QCString methodName=name();
4229 if (methodName.startsWith("operator ")) // conversion operator
4230 {
4231 methodName=substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(methodName,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4232 }
4233
4234 MemberDefMutable *imd = createMemberDef(
4235 getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),getDefColumn(),
4236 substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(m_impl->type,formalArgs,actualArgs),
4237 methodName,
4238 substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(m_impl->args,formalArgs,actualArgs),
4239 m_impl->exception, m_impl->prot,
4240 m_impl->virt, m_impl->stat, m_impl->related, m_impl->mtype,
4241 ArgumentList(), ArgumentList(), ""
4242 );
4243 imd->moveArgumentList(std::move(actualArgList));
4244 imd->setDefinition(substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(m_impl->def,formalArgs,actualArgs));
4245 imd->setBodyDef(getBodyDef());
4246 imd->setBodySegment(getDefLine(),getStartBodyLine(),getEndBodyLine());
4247 //imd->setBodyMember(this);
4248
4249 // TODO: init other member variables (if needed).
4250 // TODO: reimplemented info
4251 return imd;
4252}

4254bool MemberDefImpl::hasOneLineInitializer() const
4255{
4256 //printf("%s: init=%s, initLines=%d maxInitLines=%d userInitLines=%d\n",
4257 // qPrint(name()),qPrint(m_impl->initializer),m_impl->initLines,
4258 // m_impl->maxInitLines,m_impl->userInitLines);
4259 return !m_impl->initializer.isEmpty() && m_impl->initLines==0 && // one line initializer
4260 ((m_impl->maxInitLines>0 && m_impl->userInitLines==-1) || m_impl->userInitLines>0); // enabled by default or explicitly
4261}

4264{

4266 // initLines,userInitLines,maxInitLines);
4267 return m_impl->initLines>0 &&
4268 ((m_impl->initLines<m_impl->maxInitLines && m_impl->userInitLines==-1) // implicitly enabled
4269 || m_impl->initLines<m_impl->userInitLines // explicitly enabled
4270 );

4273void MemberDefImpl::setInitializer(const QCString &initializer)
4274{
4275 m_impl->initializer=initializer;
4276 int l=m_impl->initializer.length();
4277 int p=l-1;
4278 while (p>=0 && isspace(static_cast<uchar>(m_impl->initializer.at(p)))) p--;
4279 m_impl->initializer=m_impl->initializer.left(p+1);
4280 m_impl->initLines=m_impl->initializer.contains('\n');
4281 //printf("%s::setInitializer(%s)\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(m_impl->initializer));
4282}
4283
4284void MemberDefImpl::addListReference(Definition *)
4285{
4286 bool optimizeOutputForC = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_FOR_C);
4287 //bool hideScopeNames = Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES);
4288 //bool optimizeOutputJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
4289 //bool fortranOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_FOR_FORTRAN);
4290 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
4291 if (!isLinkableInProject()) return;
4292 QCString memLabel;
4293 if (optimizeOutputForC)
4294 {
4295 memLabel=theTranslator->trGlobal(TRUE,TRUE);
4296 }
4297 else if (lang==SrcLangExt_Fortran)
4298 {
4299 memLabel=theTranslator->trSubprogram(TRUE,TRUE);
4300 }
4301 else
4302 {
4303 memLabel=theTranslator->trMember(TRUE,TRUE);
4304 }
4305 QCString memName = name();
4306 Definition *pd=getOuterScope();
4307 QCString pdName = pd->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass ?
4308 (toClassDef(pd))->displayName() : pd->name();
4309 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
4310 QCString memArgs;
4311 if (!isRelated()
4312 /* && commented out as a result of bug 597016
4313 (
4314 (!hideScopeNames && // there is a scope
4315 pd && pd!=Doxygen::globalScope) // and we can show it
4316 ||
4317 (pd=getClassDef()) // it's a class so we
4318 // show the scope anyway
4319 )
4320 */
4321 )
4322 {
4323 if (isObjCMethod())
4324 {
4325 memName = "[" + pd->name() + " " + name() + "]";
4326 }
4327 else
4328 {
4329 if (pd!=Doxygen::globalScope) memName.prepend(pdName+sep);
4330 memArgs = argsString();
4331 }
4332 }
4333 const RefItemVector &xrefItems = xrefListItems();
4334 addRefItem(xrefItems,
4335 qualifiedName()+argsString(), // argsString is needed for overloaded functions (see bug 609624)
4336 memLabel,
4337 getOutputFileBase()+"#"+anchor(),memName,memArgs,pd);
4338}

4351
4352Specifier MemberDefImpl::virtualness(int count) const
4353{
4354 if (count>25)
4355 {
4356 warn(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),
4357 "Internal inconsistency: recursion detected in overload relation for member %s!"
4358 ,qPrint(name())
4359 );
4360 return Specifier::Normal;
4361 }
4362 Specifier v = m_impl->virt;
4363 const MemberDef *rmd = reimplements();
4364 while (rmd && v==Specifier::Normal)
4365 {
4366 v = rmd->virtualness(count+1)==Specifier::Normal ? Specifier::Normal : Specifier::Virtual;
4367 rmd = rmd->reimplements();
4368 }
4369 return v;
4370}
4371
4372void MemberDefImpl::writeTagFile(TextStream &tagFile,bool useQualifiedName) const
4373{
4374 if (!isLinkableInProject()) return;
4375 tagFile << " <member kind=\"";
4376 switch (m_impl->mtype)
4377 {
4378 case MemberType_Define: tagFile << "define"; break;
4379 case MemberType_EnumValue: tagFile << "enumvalue"; break;
4380 case MemberType_Property: tagFile << "property"; break;
4381 case MemberType_Event: tagFile << "event"; break;
4382 case MemberType_Variable: tagFile << "variable"; break;
4383 case MemberType_Typedef: tagFile << "typedef"; break;
4384 case MemberType_Enumeration: tagFile << "enumeration"; break;
4385 case MemberType_Function: tagFile << "function"; break;
4386 case MemberType_Signal: tagFile << "signal"; break;
4387 case MemberType_Friend: tagFile << "friend"; break;
4388 case MemberType_DCOP: tagFile << "dcop"; break;
4389 case MemberType_Slot: tagFile << "slot"; break;
4390 case MemberType_Interface: tagFile << "interface"; break;
4391 case MemberType_Service: tagFile << "service"; break;
4392 case MemberType_Sequence: tagFile << "sequence"; break;
4393 case MemberType_Dictionary: tagFile << "dictionary"; break;
4394 }
4395 if (m_impl->prot!=Protection::Public)
4396 {
4397 tagFile << "\" protection=\"";
4398 if (m_impl->prot==Protection::Protected) tagFile << "protected";
4399 else if (m_impl->prot==Protection::Package) tagFile << "package";
4400 else /* Private */ tagFile << "private";
4401 }
4402 if (m_impl->virt!=Specifier::Normal)
4403 {
4404 tagFile << "\" virtualness=\"";
4405 if (m_impl->virt==Specifier::Virtual) tagFile << "virtual";
4406 else /* Pure */ tagFile << "pure";
4407 }
4408 if (isStatic())
4409 {
4410 tagFile << "\" static=\"yes";
4411 }
4412 tagFile << "\">\n";
4413 if (typeString()!=QCString("@"))
4414 {
4415 tagFile << " <type>" << convertToXML(typeString()) << "</type>\n";
4416 }
4417 tagFile << " <name>" << convertToXML(useQualifiedName ? qualifiedName() : name()) << "</name>\n";
4418 tagFile << " <anchorfile>" << addHtmlExtensionIfMissing(getOutputFileBase()) << "</anchorfile>\n";
4419 tagFile << " <anchor>" << convertToXML(anchor()) << "</anchor>\n";
4420 QCString idStr = id();
4421 if (!idStr.isEmpty())
4422 {
4423 tagFile << " <clangid>" << convertToXML(idStr) << "</clangid>\n";
4424 }
4425 tagFile << " <arglist>" << convertToXML(argsString()) << "</arglist>\n";
4426 if (isStrong())
4427 {
4428 for (const auto &fmd : m_impl->enumFields)
4429 {
4430 if (!fmd->isReference())
4431 {
4432 tagFile << " <enumvalue file=\"" << convertToXML(addHtmlExtensionIfMissing(getOutputFileBase()));
4433 tagFile << "\" anchor=\"" << convertToXML(fmd->anchor());
4434 idStr = fmd->id();
4435 if (!idStr.isEmpty())
4436 {
4437 tagFile << "\" clangid=\"" << convertToXML(idStr);
4438 }
4439 tagFile << "\">" << convertToXML(fmd->name()) << "</enumvalue>\n";
4440 }
4441 }
4442 }
4443 writeDocAnchorsToTagFile(tagFile);
4444 tagFile << " </member>\n";
4445}
4446
4447void MemberDefImpl::_computeIsConstructor()
4448{
4449 m_isConstructorCached=1; // FALSE
4450 if (getClassDef())
4451 {
4452 if (m_impl->isDMember) // for D
4453 {
4454 m_isConstructorCached = name()=="this" ? 2 : 1;
4455 return;
4456 }
4457 else if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_PHP) // for PHP
4458 {
4459 m_isConstructorCached = name()=="__construct" ? 2 : 1;
4460 return;
4461 }
4462 else if (name()=="__init__" &&
4463 getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Python) // for Python
4464 {
4465 m_isConstructorCached = 2; // TRUE
4466 return;
4467 }
4468 else // for other languages
4469 {
4470 QCString locName = getClassDef()->localName();
4471 int i=locName.find('<');
4472 if (i==-1) // not a template class
4473 {
4474 m_isConstructorCached = name()==locName ? 2 : 1;
4475 }
4476 else
4477 {
4478 m_isConstructorCached = name()==locName.left(i) ? 2 : 1;
4479 }
4480 return;
4481 }
4482 }
4483}
4484
4485bool MemberDefImpl::isConstructor() const
4486{
4487 if (m_isConstructorCached==0)
4488 {
4489 MemberDefImpl *that = const_cast<MemberDefImpl*>(this);
4490 that->_computeIsConstructor();
4491 }
4492 ASSERT(m_isConstructorCached>0);
4493 return m_isConstructorCached==2;
4494
4495}
4496
4497void MemberDefImpl::_computeIsDestructor()
4498{
4499 bool isDestructor;
4500 if (m_impl->isDMember) // for D
4501 {
4502 isDestructor = name()=="~this";
4503 }
4504 else if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_PHP) // for PHP
4505 {
4506 isDestructor = name()=="__destruct";
4507 }
4508 else if (name()=="__del__" &&
4509 getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Python) // for Python
4510 {
4511 isDestructor=TRUE;
4512 }
4513 else // other languages
4514 {
4515 isDestructor =
4516 (name().find('~')!=-1 || name().find('!')!=-1) // The ! is for C++/CLI
4517 && name().find("operator")==-1;
4518 }
4519 m_isDestructorCached = isDestructor ? 2 : 1;
4520}
4521
4522bool MemberDefImpl::isDestructor() const
4523{
4524 if (m_isDestructorCached==0)
4525 {
4526 MemberDefImpl *that=const_cast<MemberDefImpl*>(this);
4527 that->_computeIsDestructor();
4528 }
4529 ASSERT(m_isDestructorCached>0);
4530 return m_isDestructorCached==2;
4531}
4532
4533void MemberDefImpl::writeEnumDeclaration(OutputList &typeDecl,
4534 const ClassDef *cd,const NamespaceDef *nd,const FileDef *fd,const GroupDef *gd) const
4535{
4536 int enumMemCount=0;
4537
4538 uint numVisibleEnumValues=0;
4539 for (const auto &fmd : m_impl->enumFields)
4540 {
4541 if (fmd->isBriefSectionVisible()) numVisibleEnumValues++;
4542 }
4543 if (numVisibleEnumValues==0 && !isBriefSectionVisible())
4544 {
4545 return;
4546 }
4547
4548 QCString n = name();
4549 int i=n.findRev("::");
4550 if (i!=-1) n=n.right(n.length()-i-2); // strip scope (TODO: is this needed?)
4551 if (n[0]!='@') // not an anonymous enum
4552 {
4553 if (isLinkableInProject() || hasDocumentedEnumValues())
4554 {
4555 //_writeTagData(compoundType);
4556 writeLink(typeDecl,cd,nd,fd,gd);
4557 }
4558 else
4559 {
4560 typeDecl.startBold();
4561 typeDecl.docify(n);
4562 typeDecl.endBold();
4563 }
4564 typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
4565 }
4566 if (!m_impl->enumBaseType.isEmpty())
4567 {
4568 typeDecl.writeChar(':');
4569 typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
4570 typeDecl.docify(m_impl->enumBaseType);
4571 typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
4572 }
4573
4574 uint enumValuesPerLine = static_cast<uint>(Config_getInt(ENUM_VALUES_PER_LINE));
4575 if (numVisibleEnumValues>0 && enumValuesPerLine>0)
4576 {
4577 typeDecl.docify("{ ");
4578
4579 auto it = m_impl->enumFields.begin();
4580 if (it!=m_impl->enumFields.end())
4581 {
4582 const MemberDef *fmd=*it;
4583 bool fmdVisible = fmd->isBriefSectionVisible();
4584 bool first=true;
4585 while (fmd)
4586 {
4587 if (fmdVisible)
4588 {
4589 if (!first)
4590 {
4591 typeDecl.writeString(", ");
4592 }
4593 /* in html we start a new line after a number of items */
4594 if (numVisibleEnumValues>enumValuesPerLine
4595 && (enumMemCount%enumValuesPerLine)==0
4596 )
4597 {
4598 typeDecl.pushGeneratorState();
4599 typeDecl.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
4600 typeDecl.enable(OutputType::Latex);
4601 typeDecl.enable(OutputType::Docbook);
4602 typeDecl.lineBreak();
4603 typeDecl.disable(OutputType::Latex);
4604 typeDecl.disable(OutputType::Docbook);
4605 typeDecl.writeString("&#160;&#160;");
4606 typeDecl.popGeneratorState();
4607 }
4608
4609 if (fmd->hasDocumentation()) // enum value has docs
4610 {
4611 fmd->writeLink(typeDecl,cd,nd,fd,gd);
4612 }
4613 else // no docs for this enum value
4614 {
4615 typeDecl.startBold();
4616 typeDecl.docify(fmd->name());
4617 typeDecl.endBold();
4618 }
4619 if (fmd->hasOneLineInitializer()) // enum value has initializer
4620 {
4621 //typeDecl.writeString(" = ");
4622 typeDecl.writeString(" ");
4623 typeDecl.parseText(fmd->initializer());
4624 }
4625 first=false;
4626 }
4627
4628 bool prevVisible = fmdVisible;
4629 ++it;
4630 if (it!=m_impl->enumFields.end())
4631 {
4632 fmd=*it;
4633 }
4634 else
4635 {
4636 fmd=0;
4637 }
4638 if (prevVisible)
4639 {
4640 typeDecl.disable(OutputType::Man);
4641 typeDecl.writeString("\n"); // to prevent too long lines in LaTeX
4642 typeDecl.enable(OutputType::Man);
4643 enumMemCount++;
4644 }
4645 }
4646 if (numVisibleEnumValues>enumValuesPerLine)
4647 {
4648 typeDecl.pushGeneratorState();
4649 typeDecl.disableAllBut(OutputType::Html);
4650 typeDecl.lineBreak();
4651 typeDecl.popGeneratorState();
4652 }
4653 }
4654 typeDecl.docify(" }");
4655 }
4656}
4657
4658void MemberDefImpl::moveArgumentList(std::unique_ptr<ArgumentList> al)
4659{
4660 m_impl->defArgList = *al;
4661}

4719bool MemberDefImpl::isObjCMethod() const

4722 return FALSE;
4723}

4736
4737QCString MemberDefImpl::qualifiedName() const
4738{
4739 if (isObjCMethod())
4740 {
4741 QCString qm;
4742 if (isStatic()) qm="+"; else qm="-";
4743 qm+="[";
4744 qm+=getClassDef()->name()+" ";
4745 qm+=name();
4746 qm+="]";
4747 return qm;
4748 }
4749 else if (m_impl->enumScope && m_impl->enumScope->isStrong())
4750 {
4751 return m_impl->enumScope->qualifiedName()+
4752 getLanguageSpecificSeparator(getLanguage())+
4753 localName();
4754 }
4755 else
4756 {
4757 return DefinitionMixin::qualifiedName();
4758 }
4759}
4760
4761void MemberDefImpl::setTagInfo(const TagInfo *ti)
4762{
4763 if (ti)
4764 {
4765 //printf("%s: Setting tag name=%s anchor=%s\n",qPrint(name()),qPrint(ti->tagName),qPrint(ti->anchor));
4766 m_impl->anc=ti->anchor;
4767 setReference(ti->tagName);
4768 m_impl->explicitOutputFileBase = stripExtension(ti->fileName);
4769 }
4770}
4771
4772QCString MemberDefImpl::objCMethodName(bool localLink,bool showStatic) const
4773{
4774 QCString qm;
4775 if (showStatic)
4776 {
4777 if (isStatic()) qm="+ "; else qm="- ";
4778 }
4779 qm+=name();
4780 if (!localLink) // link to method of same class
4781 {
4782 qm+=" (";
4783 qm+=getClassDef()->name();
4784 qm+=")";
4785 }
4786 return qm;
4787}

5330
5331void MemberDefImpl::resolveUnnamedParameters(const MemberDef *md)
5332{
5333 ArgumentList &decAl = m_impl->declArgList;
5334 ArgumentList &defAl = m_impl->defArgList;
5335 const ArgumentList &decAlSrc = md->declArgumentList();
5336 const ArgumentList &defAlSrc = md->argumentList();
5337 auto decSrc = decAlSrc.begin(), defSrc = defAlSrc.begin();
5338 for (auto decIt = decAl.begin(), defIt = defAl.begin();
5339 decIt != decAl.end() && defIt != defAl.end() && decSrc != decAlSrc.end() && defSrc != defAlSrc.end();
5340 ++decIt, ++defIt, ++decSrc, ++defSrc++)
5341 {
5342 Argument &decA = *decIt;
5343 Argument &defA = *defIt;
5344 const Argument &decAS = *decSrc;
5345 const Argument &defAS = *defSrc;
5346 if (decA.name.isEmpty())
5347 {
5348 if (!defA.name.isEmpty())
5349 {
5350 decA.name = defA.name;
5351 }
5352 else if (!decAS.name.isEmpty())
5353 {
5354 decA.name = decAS.name;
5355 }
5356 else if (!defAS.name.isEmpty())
5357 {
5358 decA.name = defAS.name;
5359 }
5360 }
5361 if (defA.name.isEmpty())
5362 {
5363 if (!decA.name.isEmpty())
5364 {
5365 defA.name = decA.name;
5366 }
5367 else if (!decAS.name.isEmpty())
5368 {
5369 defA.name = decAS.name;
5370 }
5371 else if (!defAS.name.isEmpty())
5372 {
5373 defA.name = defAS.name;
5374 }
5375 }
5376 }
5377}

5408
5409bool MemberDefImpl::_hasVisibleCallGraph() const
5410{
5411 bool enabled = m_impl->hasCallGraph &&
5412 (isFunction() || isSlot() || isSignal()) &&
5413 Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT);
5414 if (enabled)
5415 {
5416 bool trivial = DotCallGraph::isTrivial(this,FALSE);
5417 return !trivial;
5418 }
5419 return FALSE;
5420}
5421
5422bool MemberDefImpl::hasCallerGraph() const
5423{
5424 return m_impl->hasCallerGraph;
5425}
5426
5427bool MemberDefImpl::_hasVisibleCallerGraph() const
5428{
5429 bool enabled = m_impl->hasCallerGraph &&
5430 (isFunction() || isSlot() || isSignal()) &&
5431 Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT);
5432 if (enabled)
5433 {
5434 bool trivial = DotCallGraph::isTrivial(this,TRUE);
5435 return !trivial;
5436 }
5437 return FALSE;
5438}

5776
5777void MemberDefImpl::copyArgumentNames(const MemberDef *bmd)
5778{
5779 {
5780 const ArgumentList &srcAl = bmd->argumentList();
5781 ArgumentList &dstAl = m_impl->defArgList;
5782 auto srcIt = srcAl.begin();
5783 auto dstIt = dstAl.begin();
5784 while ( srcIt!=srcAl.end() && dstIt!=dstAl.end())
5785 {
5786 Argument &argDst = *dstIt;
5787 const Argument &argSrc = *srcIt;
5788 argDst.name = argSrc.name;
5789 argDst.docs = argSrc.docs;
5790 ++srcIt;
5791 ++dstIt;
5792 }
5793 }
5794
5795 {
5796 const ArgumentList &srcAl = bmd->declArgumentList();
5797 ArgumentList &dstAl = m_impl->declArgList;
5798 auto srcIt = srcAl.begin();
5799 auto dstIt = dstAl.begin();
5800
5801 while ( srcIt!=srcAl.end() && dstIt!=dstAl.end())
5802 {
5803 Argument &argDst = *dstIt;
5804 const Argument &argSrc = *srcIt;
5805 argDst.name = argSrc.name;
5806 argDst.docs = argSrc.docs;
5807 ++srcIt;
5808 ++dstIt;
5809 }
5810 }
5811}

5816 {
5817 a.canType.resize(0);
5818 }

5845
5846static void transferArgumentDocumentation(ArgumentList &decAl,ArgumentList &defAl)
5847{
5848 for (auto decIt = decAl.begin(), defIt = defAl.begin();
5849 decIt!= decAl.end() && defIt!= defAl.end();
5850 ++decIt, ++defIt)
5851 {
5852 Argument &decA = *decIt;
5853 Argument &defA = *defIt;
5854 if (decA.docs.isEmpty() && !defA.docs.isEmpty())
5855 {
5856 decA.docs = defA.docs;
5857 }
5858 else if (defA.docs.isEmpty() && !decA.docs.isEmpty())
5859 {
5860 defA.docs = decA.docs;
5861 }
5862 if (Config_getBool(RESOLVE_UNNAMED_PARAMS))
5863 {
5864 if (decA.name.isEmpty() && !defA.name.isEmpty())
5865 {
5866 decA.name = defA.name;
5867 }
5868 else if (defA.name.isEmpty() && !decA.name.isEmpty())
5869 {
5870 defA.name = decA.name;
5871 }
5872 }
5873 }
5874}
5875
5876void combineDeclarationAndDefinition(MemberDefMutable *mdec,MemberDefMutable *mdef)
5877{
5878 //printf("mdec=%s isPrototype()=%d\n",qPrint(mdec->name()),mdec->isPrototype());
5879 if (
5880 (mdef->isFunction() && !mdef->isStatic() && !mdef->isPrototype()) ||
5881 (mdef->isVariable() && !mdef->isExternal() && !mdef->isStatic())
5882 )
5883 {
5884 //printf("mdef=(%p,%s) mdec=(%p,%s)\n",
5885 // mdef, mdef ? qPrint(mdef->name()) : "",
5886 // mdec, mdec ? qPrint(mdec->name()) : "");
5887
5888 bool sameNumTemplateArgs = mdef->templateArguments().size()==mdec->templateArguments().size();
5889
5890 ArgumentList &mdefAl = const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdef->argumentList());
5891 ArgumentList &mdecAl = const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdec->argumentList());
5892 if (sameNumTemplateArgs &&
5893 matchArguments2(mdef->getOuterScope(),mdef->getFileDef(),&mdefAl,
5894 mdec->getOuterScope(),mdec->getFileDef(),&mdecAl,
5895 TRUE,mdef->getLanguage()
5896 )
5897 ) /* match found */
5898 {
5899 //printf("Found member %s: definition in %s (doc='%s') and declaration in %s (doc='%s')\n",
5900 // mn->memberName(),
5901 // qPrint(mdef->getFileDef()->name()),qPrint(mdef->documentation()),
5902 // qPrint(mdec->getFileDef()->name()),qPrint(mdec->documentation())
5903 // );
5904
5905 if (Config_getBool(RESOLVE_UNNAMED_PARAMS))
5906 {
5907 mdec->resolveUnnamedParameters(mdef);
5908 }
5909
5910 // first merge argument documentation
5911 transferArgumentDocumentation(mdecAl,mdefAl);
5912
5913 /* copy documentation between function definition and declaration */
5914 if (!mdec->briefDescription().isEmpty())
5915 {
5916 mdef->setBriefDescription(mdec->briefDescription(),mdec->briefFile(),mdec->briefLine());
5917 }
5918 else if (!mdef->briefDescription().isEmpty())
5919 {
5920 mdec->setBriefDescription(mdef->briefDescription(),mdef->briefFile(),mdef->briefLine());
5921 }
5922 if (!mdef->documentation().isEmpty())
5923 {
5924 //printf("transferring docs mdef->mdec (%s->%s)\n",mdef->argsString(),mdec->argsString());
5925 mdec->setDocumentation(mdef->documentation(),mdef->docFile(),mdef->docLine());
5926 mdec->setDocsForDefinition(mdef->isDocsForDefinition());
5927 if (mdefAl.hasParameters())
5928 {
5929 auto mdefAlComb = stringToArgumentList(mdef->getLanguage(),mdef->argsString());
5930 transferArgumentDocumentation(mdefAl,*mdefAlComb);
5931 mdec->moveArgumentList(std::move(mdefAlComb));
5932 }
5933 }
5934 else if (!mdec->documentation().isEmpty())
5935 {
5936 //printf("transferring docs mdec->mdef (%s->%s)\n",mdec->argsString(),mdef->argsString());
5937 mdef->setDocumentation(mdec->documentation(),mdec->docFile(),mdec->docLine());
5938 mdef->setDocsForDefinition(mdec->isDocsForDefinition());
5939 if (mdecAl.hasParameters())
5940 {
5941 auto mdecAlComb = stringToArgumentList(mdec->getLanguage(),mdec->argsString());
5942 transferArgumentDocumentation(mdecAl,*mdecAlComb);
5943 mdef->moveDeclArgumentList(std::move(mdecAlComb));
5944 }
5945 }
5946 if (!mdef->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
5947 {
5948 mdec->setInbodyDocumentation(mdef->inbodyDocumentation(),mdef->inbodyFile(),mdef->inbodyLine());
5949 }
5950 else if (!mdec->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
5951 {
5952 mdef->setInbodyDocumentation(mdec->inbodyDocumentation(),mdec->inbodyFile(),mdec->inbodyLine());
5953 }
5954 if (mdec->getStartBodyLine()!=-1 && mdef->getStartBodyLine()==-1)
5955 {
5956 //printf("body mdec->mdef %d-%d\n",mdec->getStartBodyLine(),mdef->getEndBodyLine());
5957 mdef->setBodySegment(mdec->getDefLine(),mdec->getStartBodyLine(),mdec->getEndBodyLine());
5958 mdef->setBodyDef(mdec->getBodyDef());
5959 //mdef->setBodyMember(mdec);
5960 }
5961 else if (mdef->getStartBodyLine()!=-1 && mdec->getStartBodyLine()==-1)
5962 {
5963 //printf("body mdef->mdec %d-%d\n",mdef->getStartBodyLine(),mdec->getEndBodyLine());
5964 mdec->setBodySegment(mdef->getDefLine(),mdef->getStartBodyLine(),mdef->getEndBodyLine());
5965 mdec->setBodyDef(mdef->getBodyDef());
5966 //mdec->setBodyMember(mdef);
5967 }
5968 mdec->mergeMemberSpecifiers(mdef->getMemberSpecifiers());
5969 mdef->mergeMemberSpecifiers(mdec->getMemberSpecifiers());
5970
5971 // copy group info.
5972 if (mdec->getGroupDef()==0 && mdef->getGroupDef()!=0)
5973 {
5974 mdec->setGroupDef(mdef->getGroupDef(),
5975 mdef->getGroupPri(),
5976 mdef->docFile(),
5977 mdef->docLine(),
5978 mdef->hasDocumentation(),
5979 mdef
5980 );
5981 }
5982 else if (mdef->getGroupDef()==0 && mdec->getGroupDef()!=0)
5983 {
5984 mdef->setGroupDef(mdec->getGroupDef(),
5985 mdec->getGroupPri(),
5986 mdec->docFile(),
5987 mdec->docLine(),
5988 mdec->hasDocumentation(),
5989 mdec
5990 );
5991 }
5992
5993
5994 mdec->mergeRefItems(mdef);
5995 mdef->mergeRefItems(mdec);
5996
5997 mdef->setMemberDeclaration(mdec);
5998 mdec->setMemberDefinition(mdef);
5999
6000 mdef->enableCallGraph(mdec->hasCallGraph() || mdef->hasCallGraph());
6001 mdef->enableCallerGraph(mdec->hasCallerGraph() || mdef->hasCallerGraph());
6002 mdec->enableCallGraph(mdec->hasCallGraph() || mdef->hasCallGraph());
6003 mdec->enableCallerGraph(mdec->hasCallerGraph() || mdef->hasCallerGraph());
6004
6005 mdef->enableReferencedByRelation(mdec->hasReferencedByRelation() || mdef->hasReferencedByRelation());
6006 mdef->enableReferencesRelation(mdec->hasReferencesRelation() || mdef->hasReferencesRelation());
6007 mdec->enableReferencedByRelation(mdec->hasReferencedByRelation() || mdef->hasReferencedByRelation());
6008 mdec->enableReferencesRelation(mdec->hasReferencesRelation() || mdef->hasReferencesRelation());
6009
6010 mdef->addQualifiers(mdec->getQualifiers());
6011 mdec->addQualifiers(mdef->getQualifiers());
6012 }
6013 }
6014}

6045bool MemberDefImpl::isFriendToHide() const
6046{
6047 bool hideFriendCompounds = Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS);
6048 bool isFriendToHide = hideFriendCompounds &&
6049 (m_impl->type=="friend class" ||
6050 m_impl->type=="friend struct" ||
6051 m_impl->type=="friend union");
6052 return isFriendToHide;
6053}

6056{

6058 (m_impl->type=="friend class" || m_impl->type=="friend struct" ||
6059 m_impl->type=="friend union"));
6060}

6084CodeSymbolType MemberDefImpl::codeSymbolType() const
6085{
6086 switch (memberType())
6087 {
6088 case MemberType_Define: return CodeSymbolType::Define;
6089 case MemberType_Function: return CodeSymbolType::Function;
6090 case MemberType_Variable: return CodeSymbolType::Variable;
6091 case MemberType_Typedef: return CodeSymbolType::Typedef;
6092 case MemberType_Enumeration: return CodeSymbolType::Enumeration;
6093 case MemberType_EnumValue: return CodeSymbolType::EnumValue;
6094 case MemberType_Signal: return CodeSymbolType::Signal;
6095 case MemberType_Slot: return CodeSymbolType::Slot;
6096 case MemberType_Friend: return CodeSymbolType::Friend;
6097 case MemberType_DCOP: return CodeSymbolType::DCOP;
6098 case MemberType_Property: return CodeSymbolType::Property;
6099 case MemberType_Event: return CodeSymbolType::Event;
6100 case MemberType_Interface: return CodeSymbolType::Interface;
6101 case MemberType_Service: return CodeSymbolType::Service;
6102 case MemberType_Sequence: return CodeSymbolType::Sequence;
6103 case MemberType_Dictionary: return CodeSymbolType::Dictionary;
6104 }
6105 return CodeSymbolType::Default;
6106}

6110
6111static std::mutex g_docCrossReferenceMutex;
6112
6113void addDocCrossReference(const MemberDef *s,const MemberDef *d)
6114{
6115 MemberDefMutable *src = toMemberDefMutable(const_cast<MemberDef*>(s));
6116 MemberDefMutable *dst = toMemberDefMutable(const_cast<MemberDef*>(d));
6117 if (src==0 || dst==0) return;
6118 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(g_docCrossReferenceMutex);
6119 //printf("--> addDocCrossReference src=%s,dst=%s\n",qPrint(src->name()),qPrint(dst->name()));
6120 if (dst->isTypedef() || dst->isEnumerate()) return; // don't add types
6121 if ((dst->hasReferencedByRelation() || dst->hasCallerGraph()) &&
6122 src->showInCallGraph()
6123 )
6124 {
6125 dst->addSourceReferencedBy(src);
6126 MemberDefMutable *mdDef = toMemberDefMutable(dst->memberDefinition());
6127 if (mdDef)
6128 {
6129 mdDef->addSourceReferencedBy(src);
6130 }
6131 MemberDefMutable *mdDecl = toMemberDefMutable(dst->memberDeclaration());
6132 if (mdDecl)
6133 {
6134 mdDecl->addSourceReferencedBy(src);
6135 }
6136 }
6137 if ((src->hasReferencesRelation() || src->hasCallGraph()) &&
6138 src->showInCallGraph()
6139 )
6140 {
6141 src->addSourceReferences(dst);
6142 MemberDefMutable *mdDef = toMemberDefMutable(src->memberDefinition());
6143 if (mdDef)
6144 {
6145 mdDef->addSourceReferences(dst);
6146 }
6147 MemberDefMutable *mdDecl = toMemberDefMutable(src->memberDeclaration());
6148 if (mdDecl)
6149 {
6150 mdDecl->addSourceReferences(dst);
6151 }
6152 }
6153}
